ADD TUTORIAL_CAT:0 "Leaving Home"
CN2 TUTORIAL_CAT:0 "离开家园"
ADD TUTORIAL_DESC:1 "During the survey of our home system we found something on [From.GetName] that did not match earlier observations made from our homeworld."
CN2 TUTORIAL_DESC:1 "在调查我们自己家园的星系时，我们在 [From.GetName] 上面找到了一点东西。这和我们从母星上面的观测结果有一定的偏差。"
ADD TROP_BIOLOGY_CAT:0 "Tropical Oddities"
CN2 TROP_BIOLOGY_CAT:0 "热带奇谭"
ADD TROP_BIOLOGY_DESC:0 "The initial data gathered from the tropical forests of [Root.GetName] indicate that something is out of the ordinary."
CN2 TROP_BIOLOGY_DESC:0 "我们从 [Root.GetName] 上热带森林收集到的初始数据表明，这里有一些异常的东西。"
ADD AST_MINING_CAT:0 "Mind the Minerals"
CN2 AST_MINING_CAT:0 "注意矿物"
ADD AST_MINING_DESC:0 "Initial analysis of the asteroid's composition points towards potentially interesting finds."
CN2 AST_MINING_DESC:0 "我们对小行星的成分进行了初步的分析，有了一些有趣的发现。"
ADD GEN_DERELICT_SHIP_CAT:0 "Distress Signal"
CN2 GEN_DERELICT_SHIP_CAT:0 "求救信号"
ADD GEN_DERELICT_SHIP_DESC:0 "Our initial scans have caught an irregular signal reminiscent of our own distress patterns."
CN2 GEN_DERELICT_SHIP_DESC:0 "我们进行了初步的探测，在我们的求救频率上面发现了一个不寻常的信号。"
ADD GEN_LOST_CARGO_CAT:0 "Odd Readings"
CN2 GEN_LOST_CARGO_CAT:0 "古怪读数"
ADD GEN_LOST_CARGO_DESC:0 "While scanning the asteroid belt our science team found some sort of irregularity."
CN2 GEN_LOST_CARGO_DESC:0 "在扫描小行星带的时候，我们的科学队伍发现了一些不寻常的东西。"
ADD GEN_OLD_WAR_CAT:0 "A Feel For Steel"
CN2 GEN_OLD_WAR_CAT:0 "钢的追寻"
ADD GEN_OLD_WAR_DESC:0 "The mineral composition of [Root.GetName] does not match projections."
CN2 GEN_OLD_WAR_DESC:0 " [Root.GetName] 上矿物的成分和预期并不相符。"
ADD GEN_SURVEY_CAT:0 "On the Surface"
CN2 GEN_SURVEY_CAT:0 "地表之上"
ADD GEN_SURVEY_DESC:0 "Our first finds on [Root.GetName] point toward more interesting discoveries to be made on the surface."
CN2 GEN_SURVEY_DESC:0 "我们对 [Root.GetName] 的初步调查表明地表上应该会有更有趣的东西等待我们发掘。"
ADD SUN_RAYS_CAT:0 "Confounding Cosmic Rays"
CN2 SUN_RAYS_CAT:0 "令人疑惑的宇宙射线"
ADD SUN_RAYS_DESC:0 "We have detected odd radiation that our Science Officer demands to investigate."
CN2 SUN_RAYS_DESC:0 "我们探测到了奇怪的宇宙射线，我们的科研专员要求对其进行调查。"
ADD WAT_PLANET_CAT:0 "Drops in the Ocean"
CN2 WAT_PLANET_CAT:0 "沧海一粟"
ADD WAT_PLANET_DESC:0 "Scans of [Root.GetName] return subtle readings of something beneath the surface."
CN2 WAT_PLANET_DESC:0 "在对 [Root.GetName] 进行扫描之后，我们得到了一些关于地表下的东西的数值，尽管不易察觉。"
ADD COLD_RESEARCH_CAT:0 "Cold Hard Potential"
CN2 COLD_RESEARCH_CAT:0 "潜在发现"
ADD COLD_RESEARCH_DESC:0 "Our Science Officer has found an anomaly. It will require extensive probing, but could garner a substantial find."
CN2 COLD_RESEARCH_DESC:0 "我们的科研专员发现了一个异常现象。需要进行一些广泛持久的探测，也许会有大量新发现。"
ADD SUN_TEAPOT_CAT:0 "Improbable Orbit"
CN2 SUN_TEAPOT_CAT:0 "不可能的轨道"
ADD SUN_TEAPOT_DESC:0 "Scanning the star unveils a small object in rapid orbit. Its small size and high velocity make it difficult for our sensors to isolate."
CN2 SUN_TEAPOT_DESC:0 "我们在扫描这颗恒星的时候，发现一个微小的物体围绕着它进行着非常快速的旋转。它实在是太小了，速度又非常快，这让我们的探测器难以分辨出来。"
ADD DES_BURIED_CAT:0 "Buried in the Sand"
CN2 DES_BURIED_CAT:0 "埋藏在沙中"
ADD DES_BURIED_DESC:0 "The desert planet [Root.GetName] seems to conceal some buried secrets."
CN2 DES_BURIED_DESC:0 "沙漠星球 [Root.GetName] 似乎埋藏着一些秘密。"
ADD AST_GEAR_CAT:0 "Astonishing Asteroids"
CN2 AST_GEAR_CAT:0 "惊人的天体"
ADD AST_GEAR_DESC:0 "Observing the massive asteroid [Root.GetName], we have found...\n\nSomething. Further investigation is warranted."
CN2 AST_GEAR_DESC:0 "我们观测了大量小行星 [Root.GetName] ，有了一些……\n\n发现。还有待进一步的调查。"
ADD TROP_CONDITIONS_CAT:0 "Among the Vines and Trees"
CN2 TROP_CONDITIONS_CAT:0 "隐藏在藤蔓和大树之间"
ADD TROP_CONDITIONS_DESC:0 "[Root.GetName] appears to hold something of interest deep within its dense jungles."
CN2 TROP_CONDITIONS_DESC:0 " [Root.GetName] 上浓密的丛林里面似乎隐藏着一些有趣的东西。"
ADD ARID_SENSOR_CAT:0 "Arid and Abandoned"
CN2 ARID_SENSOR_CAT:0 "被遗弃的不毛之地"
ADD ARID_SENSOR_DESC:0 "We have detected something out of the ordinary on the arid [From.GetPlanetMoon]. It seems like somebody has been here before us. Further investigation is needed."
CN2 ARID_SENSOR_DESC:0 "我们在贫瘠的 [From.GetPlanetMoon] 上发现了一些异乎寻常的东西。似乎有一些人在我们之前就来过这里了。具体情况有待进一步的调查。"
ADD GEN_REFUGEES_CAT:0 "Intercepted Messages"
CN2 GEN_REFUGEES_CAT:0 "截获信息"
ADD GEN_REFUGEES_DESC:0 "As we scanned [Root.GetName] we received a signal. Pattern analysis makes it out to be a distress call from a ship, but we cannot be sure. We need to track the signal to its source if we wish to know more."
CN2 GEN_REFUGEES_DESC:0 "我们在扫描 [Root.GetName] 的时候截获了一个信号。频率分析显示它是一艘船发出的求救信号，但是我们不太确定，我们需要追踪它的来源才能获得更多的消息。"
ADD CON_BIOLOGY_CAT:0 "Continental Findings"
CN2 CON_BIOLOGY_CAT:0 "大陆上的发现"
ADD CON_BIOLOGY_DESC:0 "The forests on this planetoid bear promises of interesting finds."
CN2 CON_BIOLOGY_DESC:0 "这颗小行星上的森林预示着我们会有一些有趣的发现。"
ADD TOX_PLANET_CAT:0 "Toxicity"
CN2 TOX_PLANET_CAT:0 "毒性"
ADD TOX_PLANET_DESC:0 "There appears to be deliberately-crafted structures on the planet's surface, pointing toward a past long forgotten."
CN2 TOX_PLANET_DESC:0 "这颗星球上面有人造的建筑，说明这颗星球上面有一段失落的历史。"
ADD DES_PLANET_CAT:0 "Desolate Sands"
CN2 DES_PLANET_CAT:0 "荒凉的沙漠"
ADD DES_PLANET_DESC:0 "The scorching heat of [Root.GetName] is within the expected range. However, there is more unusual data still being collected by our team. Further study is needed before a final report can be filed."
CN2 DES_PLANET_DESC:0 " [Root.GetName] 上面的高温还是在预料的范围之内的。但是，我们的队伍还收集到了很多的反常数据。在最终报告完成之前，我们还需要做更深一步的研究。"
ADD MOL_PLANET_CAT:0 "The Melting Point"
CN2 MOL_PLANET_CAT:0 "熔点"
ADD MOL_PLANET_DESC:0 "The blazing fires of [Root.GetName] might be throwing our sensors off, but we are picking up readings out of the ordinary."
CN2 MOL_PLANET_DESC:0 " [Root.GetName] 上的熊熊烈焰会使我们的探测器瘫痪，但是我们依然收集到了一些不同寻常的数据。"
ADD GEN_MYSTICAL_CAT:0 "Mystical"
CN2 GEN_MYSTICAL_CAT:0 "谜团"
ADD GEN_MYSTICAL_DESC:0 "Our survey has uncovered something that can only be described by the science team as "mystical." We would need to investigate the phenomenon in more detail to unshroud this mystery."
CN2 GEN_MYSTICAL_DESC:0 "我们的科研团队调查到了一些东西，他们现在还只能称之为一个“谜团”。我们需要得到更多关于这种现象的细节，才能真正解开这个谜团。"
ADD NUKE_PLANET_CAT:0 "The Winter of the Fallen"
CN2 NUKE_PLANET_CAT:0 "失落之冬"
ADD NUKE_PLANET_DESC:0 "The nuclear wasteland is evidently a sign of a previous civilization. Our scanners are picking up activity at certain locations that we should investigate."
CN2 NUKE_PLANET_DESC:0 "这片核废土显然说明了这里曾经也出现过一个文明。我们的探测器在某些地方侦测到了一些活跃的数据，我们应该对其进行进一步的调查。"
ADD ARID_PLANET_CAT:0 "Arid Wastes"
CN2 ARID_PLANET_CAT:0 "干燥的废料"
ADD ARID_PLANET_DESC:0 "The [From.GetPlanetMoon] is not the most welcoming of places, but if our initial scans are any indication it could hold some valuable resources."
CN2 ARID_PLANET_DESC:0 " [From.GetPlanetMoon] 并不是气候最宜人的地方，但是如果我们最初的侦测数据没有错的话，它上面可能有一些有价值的资源。"
ADD anomaly.4000.name:0 "Life Finds a Way"
CN2 anomaly.4000.name:0 "生命之道"
ADD anomaly.4000.desc:0 "It appears that some of [From.GetName]'s flora has developed effective defense mechanisms through natural selection. Numerous trees and fungi exude spores that act like a powerful acidic on non-plant organisms. Thankfully Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] has found a way to counteract some strands of these spores, making the planet's forests less threatening to us!"
CN2 anomaly.4000.desc:0 " [From.GetName] 上面的一些植物在自然选择中已经进化出了一套有效的自我防御措施。许多的树木和真菌都会释放出孢子，这些孢子对非植物的生命体来说具有非常强的酸性。还好，科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 发现了中和其中一些孢子的方法，让这颗星球上的森林不那么致命了！"
ADD anomaly.4000.a.tooltip:1 "Adds the §YAcid Jungles§! modifier to [From.GetName]:\n£blocker£ Noxious Swamp §R+3§!\n£society£ §G+2§!"
CN2 anomaly.4000.a.tooltip:1 "把§Y酸性丛林§!修正添加到 [From.GetName] 上：\n£blocker剧毒沼泽§R+3§!\n£society §G+2§!"
ADD anomaly.4005.name:1 "Fragments of Life"
CN2 anomaly.4005.name:1 "生命残片"
ADD anomaly.4005.desc:1 "It appears that the asteroid [From.GetName] and the surrounding debris originate from a former planet!\n\nDeep within the center of the asteroid we can find traces of extremely valuable alloys. There are also hints of bacterial life that has now died in the vacuum of space. This shows us that the celestial body once bore the promise of life."
CN2 anomaly.4005.desc:1 "看来小行星 [From.GetName] 以及周围的残骸原本来自一颗星球！\n\n在小行星深处，我们可以发现少量价值极高的合金。另外也发现了已死于太空之中的细菌生命残骸。这证明了这一天体曾有着孕育生命的可能。"
ADD anomaly.4005.a.tooltip:2 "Adds the §YEx-Planet§! modifier to [From.GetName]:\n£alloys£ §G+3§!"
CN2 anomaly.4005.a.tooltip:2 "添加§Y原行星§!修正至 [From.GetName] ：\n£alloys£ §G+3§!"
ADD anomaly.4010.name:0 "Lost in Space"
CN2 anomaly.4010.name:0 "迷失太空"
ADD anomaly.4010.desc:0 "The signal we intercepted was a distress call from a ship in orbit around [From.GetName]. The ship is not giving off any heat signatures and seems to be drifting. A §SSpecial Project§! has been issued to investigate what has happened to the crew."
CN2 anomaly.4010.desc:0 "我们接收到的信号来自于一艘围绕 [From.GetName] 旋转的飞船。这艘船现在没有任何热成像，似乎是在漂浮。我们已经制定了一个§S特殊项目§!来调查船员的遭遇。"
ADD anomaly.4011.desc:0 "The crew of the ship has been found dead. What is more disturbing is that they appear to have been killed by some highly advanced brain parasites, which infested them and drove them mad. Thanks to Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName]'s findings we were able to protect our own crew from being infected!"
CN2 anomaly.4011.desc:0 "船员已经全部丧生。奇怪的是，他们似乎好像是被某种极其高级的脑寄生虫杀死的。它们寄生在船员的脑子里，让他们发疯。多亏了科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 及时发现，我们的船员才没有被感染。"
ADD anomaly.4012.desc:0 "The ship in orbit around [From.From.From.GetName] was not abandoned. The crew is alive, but not well, influenced by some sort of brain parasite. With the help of our scientists they could easily be cured."
CN2 anomaly.4012.desc:0 "围绕 [From.From.From.GetName] 运行的飞船并没有被遗弃。上面的船员还活着，但是状态不好。他们受到了某种脑寄生虫的影响。我们的科学家能够轻松地治愈他们。"
ADD anomaly.4012.a:0 "Help them."
CN2 anomaly.4012.a:0 "帮助他们。"
ADD anomaly.4012.a.tooltip:0 "Establish contact with the aliens."
CN2 anomaly.4012.a.tooltip:0 "接触外星人。"
ADD anomaly.4012.b:0 "Let them perish."
CN2 anomaly.4012.b:0 "让他们毁灭吧。"
ADD anomaly.4015.name:0 "The Final Rest"
CN2 anomaly.4015.name:0 "安息"
ADD anomaly.4015.desc:0 "By what has to be beyond astronomical odds, the [Root.GetName] actually managed to pinpoint the source of the odd signals as it soared past through the asteroid belt. A tiny, alien construct. A simple scan reveals that it is some sort of a ritualistic container, holding the remains of an alien spacefarer."
CN2 anomaly.4015.desc:0 "通过对天体几率的运算， [Root.GetName] 精确地找出了那个穿过了小行星带的奇怪信号的来源。信号来源于一个小型外星物品。简单的扫描显示出它是某种信念仪式容器，里面装着某个外星宇航员的遗体。"
ADD anomaly.4015.a:0 "Let the coffin continue its voyage."
CN2 anomaly.4015.a:0 "让那个棺材继续它的旅途吧。"
ADD anomaly.4015.b:0 "Open the coffin and study the corpse."
CN2 anomaly.4015.b:0 "打开棺材，研究那具尸体。"
ADD anomaly.4015.phile:0 "Bring it to [Root.Owner.Capital.GetName] and display it in a museum."
CN2 anomaly.4015.phile:0 "把它带回 [Root.Owner.Capital.GetName] ，放在博物馆里面展出。"
ADD anomaly.4016.name:0 "[DefiledCountry.GetName]"
CN2 anomaly.4016.name:0 " [DefiledCountry.GetName] "
ADD anomaly.4016.desc:0 "A couple of days have passed since we first made contact with the [DefiledCountry.GetSpeciesNamePlural], and now they are sending us a message:\n\n"We know what you have done, [Root.GetSpeciesNamePlural]. The casket you desecrated was the final resting place of our first star traveler. We demand an apology!""
CN2 anomaly.4016.desc:0 "距离我们和 [DefiledCountry.GetSpeciesNamePlural] 的第一次接触已经过去了数天，现在他们向我们发来了一则消息：\n\n“我们知道你们做了什么， [Root.GetSpeciesNamePlural] 。你们开启的那个棺材是我们第一位星际宇航员安息之处。我们要求真诚致歉！”"
ADD anomaly.4016.tooltip:0 "Your relationship will be affected."
CN2 anomaly.4016.tooltip:0 "你们之间的关系会受到影响。"
ADD anomaly.4016.a:0 "We apologize for this transgression."
CN2 anomaly.4016.a:0 "为冒犯事件道歉。"
ADD anomaly.4016.b:0 "It is merely a dead body."
CN2 anomaly.4016.b:0 "那只是个尸体罢了。"
ADD anomaly.4016.c.spirit:0 "We will pray for the spirit of your ancestor."
CN2 anomaly.4016.c.spirit:0 "我们会为你们祖先的灵魂祈祷。"
ADD anomaly.4016.d.phobe:0 "We could not care less, alien scum!"
CN2 anomaly.4016.d.phobe:0 "外星垃圾，我们根本就不在乎！"
ADD anomaly.4020.name:0 "Leviathan Down"
CN2 anomaly.4020.name:0 "利维坦的陨落"
ADD anomaly.4020.desc:0 "Thorough scans have revealed the cause of [From.GetName]'s odd metal composition. The [From.GetPlanetMoon] is the crash site of dozens of massive spaceships, larger than anything we could have ever imagined. Their construction dates back several million years."
CN2 anomaly.4020.desc:0 "通过扫描，我们发现了 [From.GetName] 奇异矿石成分的成因。 [From.GetPlanetMoon] 是几十艘巨型飞船的坠毁地点，它们的巨大形体远远超出我们的想象。建造的时间可以追溯到几百万年前。"
ADD anomaly.4020.rocket.desc:0 "Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] has found the source of the odd mineral readings. [From.GetName] is a metaphorical graveyard for gargantuan spaceships that have been resting there for millions of years. [Root.GetLeaderName] goes on and on in the debriefing about a "profound sadness that the rockets are too broken down for even careful examination to yield results.""
CN2 anomaly.4020.rocket.desc:0 "这里的矿物数值不太正常，科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 发现了它的源头。 [From.GetName] 是巨型宇宙飞船的坟场，这里的飞船残骸已经在这里沉睡了几百万年。 [Root.GetLeaderName] 还说道，“真是太遗憾了，这些推进器损坏过于严重，仔细检测也不会有什么结果。”"
ADD anomaly.4020.rocket.desc.mach:0 "We have discovered that the source of the odd mineral readings are the remains of an unconfirmed number of abnormally large, technologically advanced spaceships. Material decomposition indicates an age of approximately 2 380 669 years. The science unit on site attempted to reverse engineer the vessels' rockets but failed due to their heavily damaged state."
CN2 anomaly.4020.rocket.desc.mach:0 "我们发现那些奇怪的矿物数值来源于一些数量不明的异常巨大而且先进的太空船残骸。矿物分解表明其年龄约为2380669年。现场的科研单位试图对其火箭进行逆向工程，但因其破损过于严重而失败了。"
ADD anomaly.4020.a:0 "The materials will surely come in handy."
CN2 anomaly.4020.a:0 "这些材料会派上用场的。"
ADD anomaly.4020.b:0 "At least the materials will be useful."
CN2 anomaly.4020.b:0 "至少这些材料还很有点用。"
ADD anomaly.4020.a.tooltip:3 "Adds the §Y$ship_graveyard$§! modifier to [From.GetName]:\n£alloys£ §G+2§!"
CN2 anomaly.4020.a.tooltip:3 "添加§Y$ship_graveyard$§!修正至 [From.GetName] ：\n£alloys£ §G+2§!"
ADD anomaly.4025.name:0 "Old Explorer"
CN2 anomaly.4025.name:0 "老探险家"
ADD anomaly.4025.desc:0 "Located in a remote part of [From.GetName], the science team of the [Root.GetName] has found an out-of-place metallic tablet.\n\nIt contains basic information about a distant system, using illustrations and what appears to be a periodic table. Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] has been able to use the information to deduce the location and potential resources of the system."
CN2 anomaly.4025.desc:0 " [Root.GetName] 的科学队伍在 [From.GetName] 上的一个偏远的地方找到了一个与之格格不入的金属板。\n\n上面有关于一个遥远恒星系的一些基本信息，还有图示和一张类似于元素周期表的东西。科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 成功地使用这些信息推断出恒星系的位置，以及其中潜在的资源。"
ADD anomaly.4025.a.tooltip:0 "Gain full §YSurvey Data§! on the distant system."
CN2 anomaly.4025.a.tooltip:0 "得到遥远恒星系的§Y勘测数据§!。"
ADD anomaly.4030.name:0 "The Servants of Sand"
CN2 anomaly.4030.name:0 "沙之仆"
ADD anomaly.4030.desc:0 "Under the dunes of [From.GetName] the science team has found a fleet of crashed fighters. Ancient, yet well preserved. They are abandoned, but the lights and engines seem to function. Why they crashed is a mystery. On the main ship bridge we found a fleet AI, capable of controlling the ships in battle. It is still active. As we approach a warning signal calls. It is programmed to activate when threatened by intruders!\nA §SSpecial Project§! can be issued to try and salvage the AI before it goes haywire, or we could destroy it and avoid the risk."
CN2 anomaly.4030.desc:0 "在 [From.GetName] 的沙丘下面，我们的科学队伍找到了坠毁的舰队。虽然很古老，但是却保存得十分完好。它们早已经被遗弃，但是引擎和照明部件似乎还能运作。它们坠毁的原因目前尚不清楚。我们在领袖飞船的飞船桥上面找到了舰队的人工智能，它能够在战斗中指挥飞船。它还能运作。我们靠近的时候，它拉响了警报。在入侵者靠近的时候它就会自动启动。\n\n我们能够施行一个§S特殊项目§!在这个人工智能发疯之前回收它。我们也可以毁了它，避免未知的风险。"
ADD anomaly.4030.a:0 "Try and take control of the AI."
CN2 anomaly.4030.a:0 "试着去控制这个人工智能。"
ADD anomaly.4030.b:0 "Destroy it before it tries anything."
CN2 anomaly.4030.b:0 "在它试图做危险的事情之前毁了它。"
ADD anomaly.4030.b.tooltip:1 "Destroys the AI.\n\nAdds the §YCrashed AI-Fleet§! modifier to [From.GetName]:\n£engineering£ §G+2§!"
CN2 anomaly.4030.b.tooltip:1 "毁掉这个人工智能。\n\n把§Y坠毁的人工智能舰队§!修正添加到 [From.GetName] 上：\n£engineering §G+2§!"
ADD anomaly.4031.desc:0 "Thankfully we were able to reprogram the AI before it turned on us. It has been repurposed to commandeer ships in our fleet, and could act as a sort of Admiral if we so choose. The AI has been transported to our homeworld, awaiting assignment."
CN2 anomaly.4031.desc:0 "谢天谢地，我们成功地在人工智能攻击我们之前为它重新编写了程序。它已经开始为我们舰队的领袖飞船服务，如果我们想的话，还能让它担任上将。这个人工智能已经被运送到我们的母星，等待指派。"
ADD anomaly.4035.name:0 "Fire of the Furnace"
CN2 anomaly.4035.name:0 "熔炉的火焰"
ADD anomaly.4035.desc:0 "We have made an interesting find on [From.GetName], however it is not related to the [From.GetPlanetMoon] itself. While conducting our usual tests we captured some odd data from a far-off system's star. Its radiation indicates that it is able to fuse together beryllium without spallation; something that should not be possible!\n\nThe science team are eager to investigate and have limited the potential stars down to two not-too-distant systems.\nConsult the §SSituation Log§! for details." #Source: http://www.forbes.com/sites/ethansiegel/2015/07/01/the-only-three-heavy-elements-in-the-universe-that-arent-made-in-stars/
CN2 anomaly.4035.desc:0 "我们在 [From.GetName] 发现了有趣的东西，不过跟 [From.GetPlanetMoon] 本身没有什么关系。我们像往常一样进行测试时，突然捕获到一颗遥远星系中的恒星传出的奇怪数据。依照该恒星的辐射情况，即使在不发生散裂的情况下也可以熔合铍，可这种事根本就是不可能的！\n\n科学小组已经迫不及待想前去一探究竟了，而且他们已经将范围缩小到两个不是很远的星系。\n\n查询§S情报日志§!获取细节。"
ADD anomaly.4035.a:0 "This could prove fruitful."
CN2 anomaly.4035.a:0 "这可能会带来巨大的收益。"
ADD anomaly.4035.poi_1:0 "First Potential Star"
CN2 anomaly.4035.poi_1:0 "第一潜在恒星"
ADD anomaly.4035.poi_2:0 "Second Potential Star"
CN2 anomaly.4035.poi_2:0 "第二潜在恒星"
ADD anomaly.4035.poi.desc:0 "One of the systems that could potentially hold the odd radiation star."
CN2 anomaly.4035.poi.desc:0 "这些星系中可能就有一个有那个散发奇怪辐射恒星。"
ADD anomaly.4037.name:0 "Correct System"
CN2 anomaly.4037.name:0 "就是这个星系"
ADD anomaly.4037.desc:0 "We seem to have found the right system! The radiation data of the local star match the ones previously encountered. A §SSpecial Project§! has been issued to perform research on the star."
CN2 anomaly.4037.desc:0 "我们找到了那个星系！这颗恒星的辐射数据和之前遇到的完全一致。我们制定了一个§S特殊项目§!来对这颗恒星进行研究。"
ADD anomaly.4038.base.desc:0 "Eureka! Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] has found that the star is formed around a miniscule wormhole, which has ripped open a dimensional rift. Rays from this other dimension has replaced the need of cosmic rays in spallation, the process of supernovae radiation reducing the beryllium-8 created in stars into a stable element. The star is thus unique in its fusion capabilities."
CN2 anomaly.4038.base.desc:0 "明白了！科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 发现这个恒星是围绕一个小型虫洞形成的，虫洞撕开了一道维度裂缝。从其他维度来的射线代替了宇宙射线，导致了元素的离散。超新星辐射导致了这颗恒星中形成的铍-8衰变成了更稳定的元素，因此这颗恒星内发生的核聚变十分特别。"
ADD anomaly.4038.maxed.desc:0 "$anomaly.4038.base.desc$\n\nThis knowledge won't expand our available technology. However, it grants us more insight into what makes the universe tick."
CN2 anomaly.4038.maxed.desc:0 "$anomaly.4038.base.desc$\n\n这些知识并不会使我们现有的科技得到提升。但是，它告诉了我们更多关于宇宙运行原理的信息。"
ADD anomaly.4038.upg.desc:0 "$anomaly.4038.base.desc$\n\nThanks to this discovery our scientists will be able to research new technology!"
CN2 anomaly.4038.upg.desc:0 "$anomaly.4038.base.desc$\n\n多亏了这个发现，我们的科学家现在能够研究新的科技了！"
ADD anomaly.4038.a:0 "We have mastered the secrets of suns."
CN2 anomaly.4038.a:0 "我们已经掌握了恒星的奥秘。"
ADD anomaly.4038.b:0 "The mysteries of the universe are slowly revealed."
CN2 anomaly.4038.b:0 "我们正在逐步揭开宇宙神秘的面纱。"
ADD anomaly.4040.name:0 "Sins of a Sun"
CN2 anomaly.4040.name:0 "恒星之罪"
ADD anomaly.4040.desc:0 "The ionizing radiation on [From.GetName] are off the charts. The [From.GetPlanetMoon] seems to either have been bombarded with nuclear warheads quite recently or been exposed to a concentrated beam of cosmic rays, perhaps from a nearby supernova. How the latter could ever be achieved is beyond Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName]."
CN2 anomaly.4040.desc:0 " [From.GetName] 的离子辐射强度已经爆表了。看起来 [From.GetPlanetMoon] 似乎最近受到了核心炸弹头的轰炸，或者是暴露在了附近超新星所发出的聚集射线束之中。后者是否能够造成这种后果科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 无从可知。"
ADD anomaly.4040.a.tooltip:1 "Adds the §RIrradiated Wasteland§! modifier to [From.GetName]:\n£blocker£ Radioactive Wasteland §R+6§!\n£physics£ §G+3§!"
CN2 anomaly.4040.a.tooltip:1 "把§R受辐射的荒地§!修正添加到 [From.GetName] 上：\n£blocker 放射性荒地 §R+6§!\n£physics §G+3§!"
ADD anomaly.4045.name:0 "Echoes from the Deep"
CN2 anomaly.4045.name:0 "深处的回声"
ADD anomaly.4045.desc:0 "After rigorous research, the crew of [Root.GetName] has only been able to detect a faint "echo" emanating deep beneath the surface of [From.GetName].\n\nThe echo resembles a life signature, however it is so distant it is hard to tell if it is real or just the instruments giving off random variations. Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName]'s crew is complaining about bad rest and long hours and cannot take much more."
CN2 anomaly.4045.desc:0 "在严苛的研究之后， [Root.GetName] 的船员探测到了一个“微弱”的回声正在从 [From.GetName] 的地底深处传来。\n\n这种回声有点像是生命信号。可是我们与它的距离实在是太远了，很难分辨它到底是生命信号，还只是一个发出随机信号的机器。科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 的手下一直在抱怨说自己得不到适当的休息，工作时间太长，自己再也受不了了。"
ADD anomaly.4045.a:0 "Calibrate the scanners and look closer to the core!"
CN2 anomaly.4045.a:0 "校正探测仪，再好好看看内核！"
ADD anomaly.4045.b:0 ""The crew cannot be trusted. An expedition is needed!""
CN2 anomaly.4045.b:0 "“我们不能相信这些船员。我们需要一次实地考察！”"
ADD anomaly.4045.c:0 "The crew's health comes first."
CN2 anomaly.4045.c:0 "船员的健康是第一位的。"
ADD anomaly.4045.d:0 "We cannot rest until we get to the bottom of this!"
CN2 anomaly.4045.d:0 "在弄清楚之前，我们绝不能停下！"
ADD anomaly.4046.desc:0 "After doing some adjustments to the ship scanners, the crew of [Root.GetName] and Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName], although exhausted and on edge, have made a startling discovery. Close to the core of [From.From.GetName] is a plankton-like lifeform that stretches across the entire [From.From.GetPlanetMoon], living in a shared consciousness with vast psionic abilities.\n\nThe lifeform is able to survive under both extreme pressures and temperatures. It can even expand itself at rapid rates. It seem to either be hibernating or... hiding, as if it knew it was being watched.\n\nA lifeform this vast in size and versatile seems technically immortal. However it does not seem like it would hinder us to colonize the [From.From.GetPlanetMoon], but it might have a negative influence on the population."
CN2 anomaly.4046.desc:0 "尽管大家都筋疲力尽了，但是在调整了飞船的探测仪后， [Root.GetName] 的船员和科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 得到了一个惊人的发现。在 [From.From.GetName] 的内核附近，有一种类似于浮游生物的生命体，它们分布于整个 [From.From.GetPlanetMoon] 。有着共同的意识，以及强大的灵能能力。\n\n这种生命体能够在极高的压力和温度下存活。它能够以极高的速度繁衍。它看起来像是在冬眠……或者是在躲避什么东西，就好像它知道自己正在被观测一样。\n\n如此巨大而拥有诸多优势的生命体，理论上来说它是永生的。不过，它看起来并不会妨碍我们对 [From.From.GetPlanetMoon] 进行殖民。但是它可能会对上面的居民产生一些负面影响。"
ADD anomaly.4046.a:0 "We should try and contact it."
CN2 anomaly.4046.a:0 "我们应该试着去和它接触。"
ADD anomaly.4046.b:0 "We could poison the ocean to kill it."
CN2 anomaly.4046.b:0 "我们可以向海中下毒并杀死它。"
ADD anomaly.4046.c:0 "Better to leave it alone."
CN2 anomaly.4046.c:0 "最好还是不要理它。"
ADD anomaly.4046.c.tooltip:1 "§YYour Empire§! gains the §RNegative Media Coverage§! modifier.\n\nAdds the §RHostile Environment§! modifier to [From.From.GetName].\n\nAdds the §YAncient One§! modifier to [From.From.GetName]:\n£society£ §G+4§!"
CN2 anomaly.4046.c.tooltip:1 "§Y帝国§!获得了§R负面媒体报道§!修正。\n\n把§R恶劣环境§!修正添加到 [From.From.GetName] 上。\n\n把§Y古神§!修正添加到 [From.From.GetName] 上：\n£society §G+4§!"
ADD anomaly.4047.desc:0 "After trying several methods of contact without an answer the team decides to try sonar pings. The sound waves cause a massive reaction in the being and every crew member falls to their knees, struck with vivid visions.\n\nThis seems to be the creatures' main form of communication. It depicts its homeworld, where it lies alone near the core basking in the warmth of the [From.From.From.GetPlanetMoon], thriving in the darkness. Then it shows our people, standing on the surface, thriving in the sunshine."
CN2 anomaly.4047.desc:0 "在多次尝试接触而没有结果后，我们的小队决定尝试一下声纳定位。声波使那个生物产生了非常大的反应，所有的成员都陷入了极其真实的幻象之中。\n\n这好像是这种生物的主要交流方式。它描述了它的家乡，那是一颗静静地躺在星核附近，沐浴着 [From.From.From.GetPlanetMoon] 的温暖的星球，是黑暗中的明星。然后它向我们展示了我们的帝国，他们正在地表的阳光下茁壮成长。"
ADD anomaly.4047.a:0 "We gladly accept this invitation."
CN2 anomaly.4047.a:0 "我们开心地接受了这份邀请。"
ADD anomaly.4047.a.tooltip:1 "§YYour Empire§! gains the §RNegative Media Coverage§! modifier.\n\nAdds the §YAncient One§! modifier to [From.From.From.GetName]:\n£society£ §G+4§!"
CN2 anomaly.4047.a.tooltip:1 "§Y帝国§!获得了§R负面媒体报道§!修正。\n\n把§Y古神§!修正添加到 [From.From.From.GetName] 上：\n£society §G+4§!"
ADD anomaly.4048.desc:0 "Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] quickly synthesizes a poison that should react well with the creature's interconnected form and spread like wildfire.\n\nAfter releasing the poison the crew stare in horror as they bear witness to an unprecedented event. [From.From.From.GetName]'s core temperature spirals out of control which causes the oceans to boil. The creature's gargantuan body also releases toxins into the atmosphere. The plankton entity must have been vital in the regulation of the [From.From.From.GetPlanetMoon]'s unstable center, as well as developed toxic defense mechanisms in order to protect itself.\n\nThe [From.From.From.GetPlanetMoon] becomes completely toxic in a matter of hours."
CN2 anomaly.4048.desc:0 "科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 很快就合成出了一种毒药，它应该会和这个生物的内在结构产生剧烈的反应，以野火之势扩散开来。\n\n在释放了毒药之后，船员们陷入到了极大的恐惧之中。他们目睹了一个史无前例的事件。 [From.From.From.GetName] 的内核温度急剧升高，导致整个海洋沸腾。生物那巨大的躯体也开始向大气中释放毒素。这个浮游生物般的东西对于 [From.From.From.GetPlanetMoon] 那不稳定的核心来说一定是至关重要的。这种毒素应该也是它在进化中得到的一种自我防御的机制。\n\n [From.From.From.GetPlanetMoon] 在几个小时之内就充满了剧毒。"
ADD anomaly.4048.a:0 "..."
CN2 anomaly.4048.a:0 "..."
ADD anomaly.4048.a.tooltip:1 "§YYour Empire§! gains the §RNegative Media Coverage§! modifier.\n\nThe §YPlanet Class§! of [From.From.From.GetName] changes to §RToxic§!.\n\nAdds the §RHostile Environment§! modifier to [From.From.From.GetName].\n\nAdds resources to [From.From.From.GetName]:\n£society£ §G+4§!"
CN2 anomaly.4048.a.tooltip:1 "§Y帝国§!获得了§R负面媒体报道§!修正\n\n [From.From.From.GetName] 的§Y行星类别§!变为§R剧毒§!。\n\n把§R恶劣环境§!修正添加到了 [From.From.From.GetName] 上。\n\n添加资源到 [From.From.From.GetName] ：\n£society §G+4§!"
ADD anomaly.4049.desc:0 "Suspicious that the crew is hiding something, Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] decided to mount an unauthorized solo-expedition to examine the planet's core. A video feed from the ships submarine shows what happened:\n\nGoing deep into the oceans of [From.From.GetName] there is only darkness, but also something... alive. Inside deep-sea caverns close to the [From.From.GetPlanetMoon]'s warm core there are webs of plankton-like vegetation, that spans the [From.From.GetPlanetMoon]'s entire crust.\n\nWhile investigating the plankton [Root.GetLeaderName] is stricken with a seizure, only to awake hours later.\n\nAfter returning to the [Root.GetName] the Science Officer is delusional and only speaks of horrors and haunted dreams."
CN2 anomaly.4049.desc:0 "很可疑，这个船员正在隐瞒什么东西。科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 决定发起一场不经批准的单枪匹马的探险，仔细检查星球的内核。船上潜艇的摄像机传回了录像带，记录了事情的经过：\n\n深入 [From.From.GetName] 的海洋，那里只有黑暗。但是，还有一些……生命。在 [From.From.GetPlanetMoon] 温暖的内核附近有一些深海洞穴。洞穴的里面有网状的、类似于浮游生物的植被，缠绕着 [From.From.GetPlanetMoon] 的整个地壳。\n\n在调查浮游生物的时候， [Root.GetLeaderName] 突然癫痫发作，在几个小时之后才醒过来。\n\n回到 [Root.GetName] 后，科研专员神志不清，一直在诉说恐惧与噩梦。"
ADD anomaly.4049.a:0 "The Science Officer probably just needs rest."
CN2 anomaly.4049.a:0 "科研专员也许只是太累了。"
ADD anomaly.4049.a.tooltip:0 "Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] gains the §RManiacal§! Trait."
CN2 anomaly.4049.a.tooltip:0 "科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 获得§R狂热§!特性。"
ADD anomaly.4049.b:0 "The Science Officer is insane. To the brig!"
CN2 anomaly.4049.b:0 "科研专员发疯了。把他抓起来！"
ADD anomaly.4049.b.tooltip:0 "Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] is permanently suspended."
CN2 anomaly.4049.b.tooltip:0 "科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 被永久革职了。"
ADD anomaly.4050.desc:0 "It has been a week since the incident on [From.From.From.GetName] when the crew of the [Root.GetName] are disturbed by a loud scream. Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] is yelling, running through the halls of the ship, going on about inexplicable pains.\n\nThe crew brings the poor scientist to the sickbay and after heavy sedation and a thorough examination concludes that [Root.GetLeaderName]'s brain has changed.\n\nAfter further tests the team startlingly realizes that their leader is now capable of telekinesis and communicating with others via telepathy. [Root.GetLeaderName] is going to get healthy, after some rest."
CN2 anomaly.4050.desc:0 " [From.From.From.GetName] 的那次事件已经过去了一个星期，当时 [Root.GetName] 的船员听到了一声惊尖叫。科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 大喊大叫，在船上横冲直撞，说自己很痛很痛什么的。\n\n船员们把他带到医务室给他打了大量镇定剂并仔细检查后确认 [Root.GetLeaderName] 的脑袋发生了改变。\n\n详细的检查最终发现这位领袖现在拥有了心灵感应能力，能够通过精神跟他人沟通。 [Root.GetLeaderName] 经过休息后会康复的。"
ADD anomaly.4050.a:0 "Glad to have you back."
CN2 anomaly.4050.a:0 "欢迎归队。"
ADD anomaly.4050.b:0 "Control yourself, Science Officer. Or else."
CN2 anomaly.4050.b:0 "控制住自己，科研专员。否则别怪大家不客气。"
ADD anomaly.4050.a.tooltip:0 "Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] gains the §GPsionics Expertise§! and §GXeno Relations Expertise§! Traits."
CN2 anomaly.4050.a.tooltip:0 "科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 获得了§G灵能专精§!和§G异星相关专精§!特性。"
ADD anomaly.4051.desc:0 "The [Root.GetName]'s crew ends their research of [From.From.GetName], thankful of finally getting some rest. Sadly there were not any useful finds, but news of the crew being well-treated spreads fast and brings forth many a good word on our homeworld. Being well-rested should also have the crew produce even better results in the long run."
CN2 anomaly.4051.desc:0 " [Root.GetName] 的船员结束了他们的 [From.From.GetName] 研究，终于能够休息整顿了。可惜他们并没有什么重大收获，但是他们受到的良好待遇很快传开了，在母星深获好评。足够的休息确保了船员们能够在未来取得更好的结果。"
ADD anomaly.4051.a.tooltip:0 "§YYour Empire§! gains the §GPositive Media Coverage§! and §GWell Rested Scientists§! modifiers."
CN2 anomaly.4051.a.tooltip:0 "§Y帝国§!获得了§G正面性的媒体关注§!和§G休息充分的科学家§!修正。"
ADD anomaly.4051.b.tooltip:0 "§YYour Empire§! gains the §GPositive Media Coverage§! and §GWell Rested Scientists§! modifiers.\n\nGives access to the §Y$edict_improved_work_environment$§! Empire Edict."
CN2 anomaly.4051.b.tooltip:0 "§Y帝国§!获得了§G正面性的媒体关注§!和§G休息充分的科学家§!修正。\n\n你解锁了§Y$edict_improved_work_environment$§!帝国法令。"
ADD anomaly.4051.a:0 "The crew's well-being is its own reward."
CN2 anomaly.4051.a:0 "船员的安好就是最大的奖励。"
ADD anomaly.4051.b:0 "This is but one way to gain efficiency."
CN2 anomaly.4051.b:0 "这是提高效率的办法之一。"
ADD anomaly.4052.desc:0 "After working day and night in order to find the reason behind the echo, the crew of [Root.GetName] have found an interesting lifeform living underneath the surface of [From.From.GetName]. Previously we could not detect it due to its amazing ability to live so close to the [From.From.GetPlanetMoon]'s core, throwing off our systems analytics.\n\nScans show it to be a type of aquatic arthropod early in its evolution, but what is most surprising is the fact that it is able to reproduce by repurposing dead matter from other lifeforms into offspring.\n\nThis information will surely help our scientists to develop new pharmaceuticals! However, news of how we treated our personnel will surely spread and displease the general populace."
CN2 anomaly.4052.desc:0 "夜以继日地研究回声的根源后， [Root.GetName] 发现了 [From.From.GetName] 地面下生活的一种生物。之前没有发觉是因为它生活在非常靠近 [From.From.GetPlanetMoon] 核心的地方，这导致我们的系统分析对它毫无效用。\n\n通过扫描我们发现它是处于进化早期阶段的海洋节肢动物，但最神奇的是它竟然能够将死去的生物物质改造成自己的后代。\n\n这个信息非常有助于我们的科学家开发新的药物！不过，我们对待我们的员工的方式肯定会散发出去，造成不良影响。"
ADD anomaly.4052.a.tooltip:3 "§YYour Empire§! gains the §GPharmaceutical Innovation§! and §RNegative Media Coverage§! modifiers."
CN2 anomaly.4052.a.tooltip:3 "§Y你的帝国§!获得了§G药物创新§!和§R负面媒体报道§!修正。"
ADD anomaly.4055.name:0 "Diamond in the Rough"
CN2 anomaly.4055.name:0 "璞玉浑金"
ADD anomaly.4055.desc:0 "After the study of [From.GetName] has concluded, Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] reports that they have found the planet to be unusually rich in minerals. This discovery was made possible in large part thanks to a certain member of the [Root.GetName] crew. [Root.GetLeaderName] praises the protégé highly."
CN2 anomaly.4055.desc:0 "对 [From.GetName] 的研究结束后，科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 汇报说他们发现这颗行星满是矿物。这个发现主要归功于 [Root.GetName] 的船员。 [Root.GetLeaderName] 对这位学徒赞赏有加。"
ADD anomaly.4055.a:0 "Offer this protégé a Science Officer position."
CN2 anomaly.4055.a:0 "把该学徒升职为科研专员。"
ADD anomaly.4055.a.tooltip:0 "Gain a new §GScientist§!.\n\n$anomaly.4055.base.tooltip$"
CN2 anomaly.4055.a.tooltip:0 "获得一位新的§G科学领袖§!。\n\n$anomaly.4055.base.tooltip$"
ADD anomaly.4055.b:0 "They do good work where they are."
CN2 anomaly.4055.b:0 "让他们继续研究 [Root.GetName] "
ADD anomaly.4055.b.tooltip:2 "\n$anomaly.4055.base.tooltip$"
CN2 anomaly.4055.b.tooltip:2 "\n$anomaly.4055.base.tooltip$"
ADD anomaly.4055.base.tooltip:2 "Adds resources to [From.From.GetName]:\n£minerals£ §G+6§!"
CN2 anomaly.4055.base.tooltip:2 "添加资源到 [From.From.GetName] ：\n£minerals §G+6§!"
ADD anomaly.4060.name:0 "The Probability Conundrum"
CN2 anomaly.4060.name:0 "概率难题"
ADD anomaly.4060.desc:0 "We have gotten a report from Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName]. It seems that a... ceramic container is circling the star [From.GetName]. Most peculiar.\n\nIt should obviously not be there, yet somehow it has managed to find its way into a close orbit.\n\nA §SSpecial Project§! can be issued to investigate the container and try to deduce how it ended up there."
CN2 anomaly.4060.desc:0 "我们收到科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 的报告。据说有一个……陶瓷容器在围绕着 [From.GetName] 恒星旋转。真奇怪。\n\n这种东西不应该出现在那么靠近轨道的地方的啊。\n\n可以发布§S特殊项目§!来研究该容器并找出它出现在那里的原因。"
ADD anomaly.4060.a:0 "A conundrum worth investigating."
CN2 anomaly.4060.a:0 "值得研究的难题。"
ADD anomaly.4060.b:0 "All questions don't have worthwhile answers."
CN2 anomaly.4060.b:0 "不是所有问题都有答案的。"
ADD anomaly.4060.spirit.b:0 "Surely this is a sign of the divine."
CN2 anomaly.4060.spirit.b:0 "这一定是神灵显灵。"
ADD anomaly.4061.desc:0 "We have tried everything in order to find out how the ceramic pot ended up in a stellar orbit. Maybe we are all crazy? Maybe it does not even exist? Guess what? We tried calculating around those facts as well! We are done. There is nothing more we can do here.\n\nThe only plus side to this is that we had tons of time to spend on philosophical and economical questions, when we could not stomach to keep investigating that damned thing."
CN2 anomaly.4061.desc:0 "我们竭尽所能试图找出这个陶瓷容器出现在恒星轨道的原因。也许这是我们的集体幻觉？也许它根本不存在？连这些可能性我们都计算过了。但是一无所获。我们尽力了。\n\n唯一的好处就是当我们再也无法忍受调查这东西时，我们可以慢慢研究哲学和经济问题。"
ADD anomaly.4061.desc.mach:0 "We have tried everything in order to find out how the ceramic container ended up in a stellar orbit. Perhaps we are all malfunctioning? Perhaps it does not even exist? <<Error!>> We attempted to calculate around those facts as well. <<Error!>>\nWe are done. There is nothing more we can do here.\n\nThe one positive aspect of this investigation is that we had excessive amounts of time to spend on theoretical and economical questions, when we could not bear to keep investigating that illogical pot."
CN2 anomaly.4061.desc.mach:0 "我们为了弄清楚这个陶瓷容器是如何进入太空轨道已经想尽了办法。或许我们都故障了？或许它根本就不存在？<<错误！>>我们在计算时也尝试过把这些情况考虑在内。<<错误！>>\n这事到此为止。我们对此已无能为力。\n\n这项调查的一个好处就是，当我们无法容忍继续调查那个不合逻辑的罐子时，我们可以花大量的时间在理论与经济问题上。"
ADD anomaly.4061.a:0 "Why? Why!? WHY!?"
CN2 anomaly.4061.a:0 "为什么？为什么！？为什么！？"
ADD anomaly.4061.a.mach:0 "My circuits hurt."
CN2 anomaly.4061.a.mach:0 "我的电路好痛。"
ADD anomaly.4061.a.tooltip:0 "Embrace the futility of life's questions.\n\n"
CN2 anomaly.4061.a.tooltip:0 "拥抱无益的生活问题。"
ADD anomaly.4061.a.tooltip.mach:0 "Embrace the futility of existence.\n\n"
CN2 anomaly.4061.a.tooltip.mach:0 "存在皆无意义。\n\n"
ADD anomaly.4062.base:0 "After almost giving up hope, studying the accursed ceramic object for so long, we have reached a breakthrough!"
CN2 anomaly.4062.base:0 "在几乎快要放弃继续研究陶瓷物体时，我们终于获得了突破！"
ADD anomaly.4062.desc.mach:0 "After an extensive period of studying the confounding ceramic object without notable results, our scientific units have finally reached a breakthrough. The object does not exist in what we [Root.Owner.GetSpeciesNamePlural] know as three-dimensional spacetime, but rather it is a projection from a higher dimension.\n\nAnalyzing it, as an umbra of a fourth dimensional object, we have accumulated enough data to decrypt its message. The object teaches us how to attain improvements in all fields of research.\n\nOnly one question remains: Who or what sent this information?"
CN2 anomaly.4062.desc.mach:0 "在花了大量时间研究那个陶器物体却并未取得明显进展之后，我们的科研单位终于有了突破。该物体并不存在于我们 [Root.Owner.GetSpeciesNamePlural] 所知的三维空间中，而是一个来自更高维度的投影。\n\n分析这个四维物体的本影让我们积累了足够的数据来解密它的信息。该物体教会我们如何在所有科研领域取得进展。\n\n现在只剩下一个问题：是谁，或者是什么东西发送了这个信息？"
ADD anomaly.4062.desc:0 "$anomaly.4062.base$ The object isn't really there, but rather it is a projection from a higher dimension. Analyzing it, as a shadow of a fourth dimensional object, we have accumulated enough data to decrypt its message. The object teaches us how to improve in all fields of research.\n\nThe only question now is... who sent this information?"
CN2 anomaly.4062.desc:0 "$anomaly.4062.base$该物体并非真是存在于那里，而是从更高级的维度投影下来的。分析发现，那是一个四维物体的影子，我们累积了足够的数据去解码它的信息。该物体能够改善我们对所有研究领域的认知。\n\n现在唯一的问题是……究竟是谁发来的这道信息？"
ADD anomaly.4062.spirit.desc:0 "$anomaly.4062.base$ The container is a sacred relic, left in orbit as a sign, surely from the divine!\n\nThe object is brimming with energy, which when decrypted reveals its hidden message: information on how to help us ascend by improving our research efforts!\n\nThe only question now is... who sent this message?"
CN2 anomaly.4062.spirit.desc:0 "$anomaly.4062.base$该容器是一个神圣文物，无疑是由神灵留在轨道上的信号！\n\n该物体散发着能源，解码后终于显示出隐藏的信息：那是能够改善我们的研究能力以助我们尽早升天的信息！\n\n现在唯一的问题是……究竟是谁发来的这道信息？"
ADD anomaly.4062.spirit.a:0 "Thanks to the powers that be!"
CN2 anomaly.4062.spirit.a:0 "谢天谢地！"
ADD anomaly.4065.name:0 "Mining Your Own Business"
CN2 anomaly.4065.name:0 "采好你自己的矿"
ADD anomaly.4065.desc:0 "Deep within a crevice of the giant asteroid [From.GetName] we have found something astonishing. There is mining gear attached to the rock, digging itself into the vast depth of the asteroid! It stands abandoned, with no sign of who placed it there.\n\nIf we can stop the machine we might be able to learn something about the technology used to build it, but we must hurry before random debris crushes it."
CN2 anomaly.4065.desc:0 "在巨型小行星 [From.GetName] 的地表下，我们发现了让人叹为观止的东西。小行星深处有一部采矿设备，一直挖到小行星地核深处！看情况它是被遗弃了，没有任何痕迹显示是谁留下的。\n\n如果我们能够把这部机器停下，我们也许能够从中学习到制造它的科技，但一定要趁早，免得它被瓦砾什么的压碎。"
ADD anomaly.4065.a:0 "Try and stop the machine."
CN2 anomaly.4065.a:0 "试着把机器停下。"
ADD anomaly.4066.upg.desc:0 "We managed to stop the excavator before it broke down. It's a remarkable piece of machinery, with a smooth surface covered in diamonds. At first glance the whole drill seems like one solid piece, but it's simply so well put together that you cannot notice the grooves and joints.\n\nOur engineers will be able to reverse engineer some of this technology."
CN2 anomaly.4066.upg.desc:0 "我们成功在挖掘机损坏之前制止了它。真是个神奇的机器，它的平滑的表层完全被钻石所覆盖。乍看之下，它似乎是一个整体，但其实只是做工精良，让人难以发现其连接处。\n\n我们的工程师可以利用逆向工程研究它的科技。"
ADD anomaly.4066.res.desc:0 "We managed to stop the excavator before it broke down. Sadly it is close to our own designs, and we can't really learn anything new from it. Thankfully the depths it carved out into the rock will make it easier to find valuable minerals."
CN2 anomaly.4066.res.desc:0 "我们成功在挖掘机损坏之前制止了它。可惜它其实跟我们当前的设计非常类似，没有什么值得学习的。不过它挖出的洞可以让我们更轻易地找到贵重矿物。"
ADD anomaly.4066.b.tooltip:1 "Adds resources to [From.From.From.GetName]:\n£minerals£ §G+3§!"
CN2 anomaly.4066.b.tooltip:1 "添加资源到 [From.From.From.GetName] ：\n£minerals §G+3§!"
ADD anomaly.4070.name:0 "Fruitful Endeavors"
CN2 anomaly.4070.name:0 "重大收获"
ADD anomaly.4070.desc:0 "Good news! We have found the tropical forests of [From.GetName] to be host to a special kind of tree, blooming with nutritious fruits. The food produced stores tons of energy and contains all the chemicals our people need to function well. This will most assuredly make life a little bit easier to sustain, would we want to colonize."
CN2 anomaly.4070.desc:0 "好消息！我们发现 [From.GetName] 的热带雨林中生长着一种特殊的树，它的果实非常有营养。这种食物容纳着惊人的能源以及我们的帝国所需的所有营养。如果我们将来要在此殖民的话，这将有助于减轻我们殖民地的压力。"
ADD anomaly.4070.a:0 "Good news indeed!"
CN2 anomaly.4070.a:0 "的确是好消息！"
ADD anomaly.4075.name:0 "Strength from Small Places"
CN2 anomaly.4075.name:0 "小体量，大力量"
ADD anomaly.4075.desc:0 "Having probed the frozen landscapes of the [From.GetPlanetMoon] [From.GetName] we think we have struck something big. Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] speaks of a bacterial lifeform unlike any other. It bonds with other individuals to form large "blankets" that are durable yet light, and also acts like solar cells. They absorb solar energy with a surprisingly low efficiency loss percentage, most likely a result of evolution favoring those who could gather more heat in the harsh climate.\n\nOur researchers back home could surely find some use of this information."
CN2 anomaly.4075.desc:0 "勘测过 [From.GetPlanetMoon]  [From.GetName] 的冰冻地面后，我们获得了重大发现。科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 报告说发现了一种独一无二的细菌生物。它会跟其他个体连接起来组成巨大的“毯子”，这种毯子既轻便耐用，又能用作太阳能电池。它们能够非常高效地转化吸收到的太阳能，也许是为了在这种环境下尽可能吸收多的热能而进化出来的。\n\n我们的研究人员一定能够从这些信息中找到有用的资料。"
ADD anomaly.4075.a:0 "Find out if it can improve energy production."
CN2 anomaly.4075.a:0 "分析它是否能够改善能源生产。"
ADD anomaly.4075.b:0 "Try and find a military use."
CN2 anomaly.4075.b:0 "试图寻找战斗用途。"
ADD anomaly.4075.a.tooltip:0 "Send to our homeworld for study. Results will take a while to process."
CN2 anomaly.4075.a.tooltip:0 "送回去母星作研究。需要一段时间才能出结果。"
ADD anomaly.4076.desc:0 "Our energy development researchers have made progress with the samples we sent them from [From.From.GetName]! They have been able to develop a new type of solar cell using the organisms as a template. These are much more efficient at storing energy and will provide a boost to all our power plants."
CN2 anomaly.4076.desc:0 "我们的能源开发研究员从我们发过去的 [From.From.GetName] 样本中取得了进展！他们利用该生物为模板，成功开发了一种新的太阳能电池。这种电池能够更高效地储存能源并提高我们所有发电站的效率。"
ADD anomaly.4077.desc:0 "Our military development researchers have made progress with the samples we sent them from [From.From.GetName]! They have reconstructed the biological solar cells and documented how they retain heat energy within themselves without taking damage. This has helped them develop a new defensive technology for our fleets."
CN2 anomaly.4077.desc:0 "我们的战斗开发研究员从我们发过去的 [From.From.GetName] 样本中取得了进展！他们改造了生物太阳能电池并分析了它们是如何储存热能而让自身不受伤害。这将有助于开发一种全新的舰队防御科技。"
ADD anomaly.4080.name:0 "Abandoned Sensor Array"
CN2 anomaly.4080.name:0 "被遗弃的传感阵列"
ADD anomaly.4080.desc:0 "We have found a sensor array, solemnly standing watch on [From.GetName]. The [From.GetPlanetMoon] has no primitive life to speak of, so it must be an abandoned outpost. It was built recently, but is not functioning.\n\nIt would require both repairs and research to bring it back into working condition, while breaking it apart could allow us to learn something new from it."
CN2 anomaly.4080.desc:0 "我们在 [From.GetName] 发现了一个传感列阵。 [From.GetPlanetMoon] 星球上没有任何原始生命，所以这一定是个被遗弃的前哨。它的年代不算久远，但却无法使用了。我们需要修理并研究它才能让它恢复运作，不过要是拆毁它也许能够让我们学习到新的技术。"
ADD anomaly.4080.a:0 "Try to activate it."
CN2 anomaly.4080.a:0 "尝试启动。"
ADD anomaly.4080.b:0 "Dismantle and reverse engineer it."
CN2 anomaly.4080.b:0 "拆毁并利用逆向工程技术研究它。"
ADD anomaly.4080.c:0 "Leave it alone in case the owner returns."
CN2 anomaly.4080.c:0 "不管它，也许它的主人会归来。"
ADD anomaly.4081.desc:0 "Months of work have finally paid off! The sensor array on [From.From.From.GetName] is once again functioning and it appears to be able to give us a vastly improved sensor range of the nearby area. However, the array needs more energy and personnel to work, so a colony is needed in order to supply it with energy."
CN2 anomaly.4081.desc:0 "无数个月的工作终于开花结果了！ [From.From.From.GetName] 的传感列阵终于恢复运作了，现在我们在附近一带的扫描范围更加广泛了。不过传感列阵需要更多的能源和工人才能正常运行，所以我们需要建立一个殖民地来维持它。"
ADD anomaly.4081.a.tooltip:0 "Adds the §GSuperior Sensor Array§! modifier to [From.From.From.GetName]."
CN2 anomaly.4081.a.tooltip:0 "添加§G高级传感列阵§!修正到 [From.From.From.GetName] 。"
ADD anomaly.4081.b.tooltip:0 "Gives access to the §Y$edict_super_sensors$§! Empire Edict.\n\nAdds the §GSuperior Sensor Array§! modifier to [From.From.From.GetName]."
CN2 anomaly.4081.b.tooltip:0 "解锁§Y$edict_super_sensors$§!帝国法令。\n\n添加§G高级传感列阵§!修正到 [From.From.From.GetName] 。"
ADD anomaly.4085.name:0 "Adrift"
CN2 anomaly.4085.name:0 "漂浮"
ADD anomaly.4085.desc:0 "Among the asteroids surrounding [From.GetName], we have discovered an alien ship adrift. It is not responding to our attempts to hail them. If this is due to it being unable to interpret our signal, or some other reason, we do not know.\nScience Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] recommends that we get a construction ship to tow it out of the debris field. If left untouched, it risks being crushed by the asteroids.\n\nA §SSpecial Project§! has been issued to save the ship and investigate it."
CN2 anomaly.4085.desc:0 "在围绕着 [From.GetName] 的小行星中，我们发现了一艘外星飞船漂浮在那里。我们试图跟它取得联系，但是它毫无反应。它到底是听不明白我们的信息，还是因为别的原因无视我们，我们无从得知。\n\n科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 建议我们找一艘工程船来拖拉它出碎片区。要是不管它的话，它很可能会被小行星撞碎。\n\n已发布一项§S特殊项目§!去拯救飞船并调查它。"
ADD anomaly.4086.desc:0 "Once the ship drifting by [From.From.From.GetName] had been towed out of the debris, we could send in an away team to investigate. It is a murder scene. Only one crew member has been found - a long-eared, amphibian biped who appears to have been stabbed repeatedly. The ship is, by the death of its crew, up for grabs.\n\nIt is fitted with very efficient thrusters, the structure and design of which are beyond us at present. The vessel is not armed, seemingly having been used as a transport for important personnel.\n\nRepurposing it into an exploration vessel would be a minor undertaking. However, if we instead deconstruct it and study the engines in greater detail, we could maybe capture some of its genius and translate it into practical improvements for our fleets."
CN2 anomaly.4086.desc:0 "漂浮在 [From.From.From.GetName] 的飞船被拖拉出来，我们就能派遣特遣队去调查它。里面发生过一场战斗，只有一位船员还活着——那是一个长耳朵的两栖双腿生物，他身上有多处刺伤。该飞船因为没有了主人，归你所有了。\n\n飞船拥有非常高效的推进器，它的架构和设计都远远高于我们当前的水准。飞船没有装备武器，看来是一艘运送重要人员的运输船。\n\n把它改造成勘探船无需花费多大功夫。不过，如果我们拆毁它并仔细研究它的引擎，也许就能够对我们的舰队水平有实际提升。"
ADD anomaly.4087.desc:0 "Once the ship drifting by [From.From.From.GetName] had been towed out of the debris, we could send in an away team to investigate. The crew is still alive!"
CN2 anomaly.4087.desc:0 "只要把漂浮在 [From.From.From.GetName] 的飞船拖拉出来，我们就能派遣特遣队去调查它。上面的船员还活着！"
ADD anomaly.4086.a:0 "Repurpose it into a science vessel."
CN2 anomaly.4086.a:0 "改造成科学考察飞船。"
ADD anomaly.4086.a.tooltip:0 "Gain a §YScience§!-class ship.\n"
CN2 anomaly.4086.a.tooltip:0 "获得一艘§Y科研船§!。"
ADD anomaly.4086.b:0 "Tear it down and study the engines.\n"
CN2 anomaly.4086.b:0 "拆卸并研究其引擎。"
ADD anomaly.4086.b.tooltip:0 "§YYour Empire§! gains the §GEnhanced Ship Speed§! Modifier.\n"
CN2 anomaly.4086.b.tooltip:0 "§Y帝国§!获得了§G船速提高§!修正。"
ADD anomaly.4090.name:0 "On the Run"
CN2 anomaly.4090.name:0 "逃难"
ADD anomaly.4090.desc:0 "We successfully traced the signal! Another ship drifts, hidden, in orbit around [From.GetName]. The aliens on board hailed us, yet we do not understand each other's languages. It appears that they are refugees from their barren homeworld below. They are clearly in desperate need of a new place to live."
CN2 anomaly.4090.desc:0 "我们成功追踪到信号了！ [From.GetName] 的轨道附近藏着另一艘船。船上的外星种群回复了我们，但是我们都不明白彼此的语言。他们似乎是这颗荒芜母星的难民，正在寻找新的家园。"
ADD anomaly.4090.a:0 "They can settle on [refugee_planet_1.GetName]."
CN2 anomaly.4090.a:0 "让他们居住在 [refugee_planet_1.GetName] 。"
ADD anomaly.4090.b:0 "Let them stay on [refugee_planet_2.GetName]."
CN2 anomaly.4090.b:0 "让他们居住在 [refugee_planet_2.GetName] 。"
ADD anomaly.4090.c:0 "They might fit in on [refugee_planet_3.GetName]."
CN2 anomaly.4090.c:0 "让他们居住在 [refugee_planet_3.GetName] 。"
ADD anomaly.4090.d:0 "Let them move to [refugee_planet_4.GetName]."
CN2 anomaly.4090.d:0 "让他们居住在 [refugee_planet_4.GetName] 。"
ADD anomaly.4090.e:0 "Sadly we cannot fit them on any of our worlds."
CN2 anomaly.4090.e:0 "可惜，我们没有任何行星可以收容他们。"
ADD anomaly.4090.f:0 "Sorry, but we will not help you."
CN2 anomaly.4090.f:0 "抱歉，我们帮不到你们。"
ADD anomaly.4090.g:0 "We will not play host to aliens!"
CN2 anomaly.4090.g:0 "我们不欢迎外星人！"
ADD anomaly.4090.uninhabitable:0 "Sadly, our worlds are inhospitable to their environmental needs."
CN2 anomaly.4090.uninhabitable:0 "很不幸，我们的星球无法适应他们的生存所需。"
ADD anomaly.4093.name:0 "[RefugeeAliensNation.GetName]"
CN2 anomaly.4093.name:0 " [RefugeeAliensNation.GetName] "
ADD anomaly.4093.desc:0 "The alien refugees we once met, without the ability to communicate with one another, now stand before us on our screens.\n\n"Our peoples' paths merge again, [From.GetSpeciesAdj]. Now that we have finally found our new haven. The universe is almost cruel in its irony...\nDo you have any idea of the struggles we've been through to get here?""
CN2 anomaly.4093.desc:0 "我们曾经遇见过的缺乏沟通的能力的外星难民，现在出现在我们的屏幕前。\n\n“我们两个种群再次相遇了， [From.GetSpeciesAdj] 。现在我们终于找到了我们的新避风港，真是天无绝人之路……\n\n你知道我们历经了多少辛苦才到达这里吗？”"
ADD anomaly.4093.a:0 "Our apologies for earlier!"
CN2 anomaly.4093.a:0 "之前的事真的很抱歉！"
ADD anomaly.4093.b:0 "Everyone needs to stand on their own."
CN2 anomaly.4093.b:0 "唯有自立，才能活下去。"
ADD anomaly.4093.c:0 "With no way of communication we turned to fear."
CN2 anomaly.4093.c:0 "因为无法沟通，所以我们害怕。"
ADD anomaly.4093.d:0 "Your survival is of no concern to us, alien."
CN2 anomaly.4093.d:0 "你的生死与我们无关，异族。"
ADD anomaly.4094.apology.desc:0 ""Your apology is accepted, yet we can only imagine how many more of our kind would be here today had you helped us earlier. Farewell for now.""
CN2 anomaly.4094.apology.desc:0 "“我们接受你的道歉，但要是当初你们帮助了我们，我们就不会死去那么多人了。再见了。”"
ADD anomaly.4094.insult.desc:0 ""That is an easy stance to take, [From.GetSpeciesAdj]. Especially when you are the one standing firmly with both feet on the ground. So stand proud, as you will most assuredly stand alone. Farewell.""
CN2 anomaly.4094.insult.desc:0 "“说得轻巧， [From.GetSpeciesAdj] 。尤其是对你这种站着说话不腰疼的人来说。继续袖手旁观吧，然后你便会孤立无援。再见了。”"
ADD anomaly.4094.neutral.desc:0 ""Understandable, [From.GetSpeciesAdj]. However it will not erase our pain, being left to survive in the great void without aid. Farewell.""
CN2 anomaly.4094.neutral.desc:0 "“可以理解， [From.GetSpeciesAdj] 。不过这对我们遭受到的痛苦毫无帮助。我们曾经在最需要帮助的时候孤苦无助。再见了。”"
ADD anomaly.4094.xenophobe.desc:0 ""Right, [From.GetSpeciesAdj]. It is good to know that we had you sized up from the start. Farewell.""
CN2 anomaly.4094.xenophobe.desc:0 "“呵呵， [From.GetSpeciesAdj] 。还好我们从一开始就看透了你们。再见了。”"
ADD anomaly.4094.a:0 "Farewell."
CN2 anomaly.4094.a:0 "再见了。"
ADD anomaly.4095.name:0 "Sanctuary"
CN2 anomaly.4095.name:0 "庇护所"
ADD anomaly.4095.desc:0 "The forests of [From.GetName] have blown the crew's expectations away. It is not only a highly developed world rich in organic life, but most plant roots are even edible. This might not sound appetizing, but it indicates that we could easily grow food on this [From.GetPlanetMoon], due to the rich soil."
CN2 anomaly.4095.desc:0 " [From.GetName] 的森林让船员们大吃一惊。这不仅仅是一个充斥着各种有机生物的高度发展的世界，而且大部分植物的根茎都能吃。或许不算美味，但这代表我们可以轻易地在 [From.GetPlanetMoon] 的肥沃土壤上耕种。"
ADD anomaly.4095.a.tooltip:0 "Adds the §GLush Planet§! modifier to [From.GetName]."
CN2 anomaly.4095.a.tooltip:0 "添加§G青葱行星§!修正到 [From.GetName] 。"
ADD anomaly.4100.name:0 "The Rulers of the Water Plains"
CN2 anomaly.4100.name:0 "水上王者"
ADD anomaly.4100.desc:0 "$anomaly.4100.base.desc$ The dark scales of the creatures are rock hard, and they are very skittish when approached.\n\nIt might be possible to domesticate the beasts and have them assist in potential future colonization of the planet. However, we might however happen across some interesting revelations by studying them first."
CN2 anomaly.4100.desc:0 "$anomaly.4100.base.desc$这些生物的暗色鳞片非常坚硬，而且当有人靠近时，它们就害羞地迅速逃走了。\n\n也许可以驯服这些猛兽让它们帮忙殖民这颗行星。但先研究它们也许会有所收获。"
ADD anomaly.4100.expert.desc:0 "$anomaly.4100.base.desc$\n\n[Root.GetLeaderName] have been able to deduce that the animals have some sort of psionic ability, as changes in their demeanor indicates that they are able to intuitively sense our intentions.\n\nIt might be possible to domesticate the beasts and have them assist in potential future colonization of the planet. However, we might however happen across some interesting revelations by studying them first.\n\n[Root.GetLeaderName] claims that the indigenous creatures seem to "respond negatively to thoughts that indicate any sort of threat.""
CN2 anomaly.4100.expert.desc:0 "$anomaly.4100.base.desc$\n\n [Root.GetLeaderName] 发现这种动物有某种灵能能力，从它们的行为变化上看，它们可以感应到我们的意图。\n\n也许可以驯服这些猛兽让它们帮忙殖民这颗行星。但先研究它们也许会有所收获。\n\n [Root.GetLeaderName] 说这些当地生物会“对不怀好意的人反馈负面回应”。"
ADD anomaly.4100.base.desc:0 "On [From.GetName], Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] has discovered a race of quadraped mammalians who appear very strong and physically resilient. They run across shallow plains of water, with lush plants reaching for their legs."
CN2 anomaly.4100.base.desc:0 "在 [From.GetName] 上，科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 发现了一种身强体壮的四脚哺乳生物。他们可以徒步越过浅水处，那些青翠的植物也仅仅达到它们的腿部。"
ADD anomaly.4100.a:0 "Study them to find out more."
CN2 anomaly.4100.a:0 "研究它们，找出更多信息。"
ADD anomaly.4100.b:0 "Try to domesticate them right away."
CN2 anomaly.4100.b:0 "立刻试图驯服它们。"
ADD anomaly.4100.c:0 "Let them roam free."
CN2 anomaly.4100.c:0 "让它们自在地生活。"
ADD anomaly.4101.desc:0 "Our attempts to study the animals up close has yielded few results. They run away or fight back as soon as we approach, as if they knew we are coming way before we have even sighted their herds.\n\nThe beasts clearly understand what we are trying to do, somehow, and avoid being in close proximity to us.\n\nAt least we can keep studying them from afar and maybe learn something interesting."
CN2 anomaly.4101.desc:0 "我们试图靠近它们做研究，但进展并不顺利。它们一发现我们靠近，就要么逃走要么战斗，它们好像从大老远就能发现我们。\n\n这些动物明显清楚我们的意图，所以尽量避免跟我们接触。\n\n至少我们可以从远距离研究它们，也许会有所发现。"
ADD anomaly.4101.a:0 "A strong-willed animal to say the least."
CN2 anomaly.4101.a:0 "这最起码是一种意志坚定的动物。"
ADD anomaly.4102.desc:0 "Approaching the animals have yielded results! They appear to have psionic capabilities, able to communicate with each other, and us, via telepathy.\n\nThey wish to be free, roam the land and eat of its fruits. We would have their support, as fellow creatures of the cosmos, if we simply allow them their space and leave their food sources untouched.\n\nPositive stories of how this situation was resolved is bound to spread to the general populace."
CN2 anomaly.4102.desc:0 "接触这些动物的进展相当顺利！它们似乎拥有一种灵能感应，可以通过精神彼此沟通以及跟我们沟通。\n\n它们想要自在地生活在大地上，尽情享受那里的水果。如果我们不打扰它们的生存空间和食物，它们愿意在必要时帮助我们。\n\n这段正能源满满的接触将会被广泛传播到人们的耳中。"
ADD anomaly.4102.b:0 "We need the food for ourselves."
CN2 anomaly.4102.b:0 "我们自己也需要食物。"
ADD anomaly.4103.desc:0 "The animals are proving difficult to tame. In order to get even close to them we have to use some force and eventually sedate them. They consistently fight back when we try to put them to work. We will have to force them to perform their tasks, which hasn't turned out to be very efficient."
CN2 anomaly.4103.desc:0 "这些动物非常难以驯服。为了靠近它们，我们被迫使用了麻醉剂。我们要驱使它们的时候，它们总是反抗。我们必须强迫它们完成工作，但效果不太好。"
ADD anomaly.4103.a:0 "Wonder why they resist so?"
CN2 anomaly.4103.a:0 "它们为什么要反抗呢？"
ADD anomaly.4104.desc:0 "The animals have been difficult to work with. While we have been as gentle as possible in our advance, some of them still flee and resist. We have gathered the calmer specimens and made them work the earth for tests. Some rejected that too. We now have a small selection of individuals that are willing to help us, but they will not be as effective as the entire herd.\n\nThe way we enslaved these animals may paint us in a bad light, once word spreads to the general populace."
CN2 anomaly.4104.desc:0 "这些动物非常难以相处。虽然我们已经尽可能地温柔了，但其中一部分还是逃走和反抗。我们聚集了比较温驯的一批，训练它们工作。但其中一部分还是抗拒了。我们现在只有一小群个体愿意帮忙我们，但这相比整支帝国的参加，这样做明显低效了很多。\n\n我们驯服这些动物的消息一旦传入大众耳中，可能会对我们的声誉造成负面影响。"
ADD anomaly.4104.a:0 "Always something."
CN2 anomaly.4104.a:0 "还是有用的嘛。"
ADD anomaly.4105.name:0 "The Fumes Lie Thick"
CN2 anomaly.4105.name:0 "驱之不散"
ADD anomaly.4105.desc:0 "The planet [From.GetName] is a toxic wasteland, but our scans unveil that it has not always been so. A now extinct civilization seems to have destroyed its home planet, via a heavy reliance on climate altering fuels and toxins.\n\nOn a remote hill, close to a major city, we have found a lone active facility. A robot assembly plant, desolated and surrounded by military vehicles, so deteriorated they break upon touch.\n\nThe facility is alien and mysterious, but could provide us with ample study material."
CN2 anomaly.4105.desc:0 " [From.GetName] 行星是一个有毒废土，但是我们的扫描发现这里曾经不是现在这样的。一个如今已消灭的文明因为过度依赖改变气候的液体和毒素而彻底毁了自己的这个母星。\n\n在一个大城市附近的一处偏僻山丘上，我们发现了一座还能运行的设施。这是一个组装机器人的工厂，周围泊满了战斗车辆。但这些车辆稍稍一碰就化成了尘埃。\n\n这座设施非常神秘奇特，但也许能够提供不少研究材料。"
ADD anomaly.4105.desc.mach:0 "The planet [From.GetName] is a toxic, corrosive wasteland, but our scans unveil that it has not always been so. A now extinct organic civilization seems to have destroyed its home planet, via a heavy reliance on climate altering fuels and toxins.\n\nOn a remote hill, close to a major city, we have found a lone active facility. A robot assembly plant, desolated and surrounded by military vehicles, so deteriorated they break upon touch.\n\nThe facility is alien and mysterious, but could provide us with ample study material."
CN2 anomaly.4105.desc.mach:0 " [From.GetName] 星球是一片剧毒而腐蚀性的废土，但我们的扫描发现它并非一直如此。一个现已灭绝的有机体文明似乎因重度依赖改变气候的燃料与毒素，而摧毁了自己的母星。\n\n在靠近一座大型城市的偏远的山丘上，我们发现了一个活动的设施。这是一个荒弃的机器人组装工厂，周围泊满了严重腐朽的战斗车辆，稍稍一碰就化成了尘埃。\n\n这座设施非常神秘奇特，但也许能够提供不少研究材料。"
ADD anomaly.4105.a.tooltip:1 "Adds the §YFallen Robotic Society§! modifier to [From.GetName]:\n£engineering£ §G+6§!"
CN2 anomaly.4105.a.tooltip:1 "添加§Y失落的机械社会§!修正到 [From.GetName] ：\n£engineering §G+5§!"
ADD anomaly.4105.a:0 "A cautionary tale."
CN2 anomaly.4105.a:0 "可引以为戒。"
ADD anomaly.4105.a.mach:0 "Organics are often short-sighted."
CN2 anomaly.4105.a.mach:0 "有机体通常目光短浅。"
ADD anomaly.4105.b.tooltip:1 "Gives access to the §Y$edict_renewable_energy$§! Empire Edict.\n\nAdds the §YFallen Robotic Society§! modifier to [From.GetName]:\n£engineering£ §G+6§!"
CN2 anomaly.4105.b.tooltip:1 "解锁§Y$edict_renewable_energy$§!帝国法令。\n\n添加§Y失落的机械社会§!修正到 [From.GetName] ：\n£engineering §G+5§!"
ADD anomaly.4105.robot:0 "Try and activate the robots."
CN2 anomaly.4105.robot:0 "试图启动机器人。"
ADD anomaly.4106.desc:0 "The facility on [From.From.From.GetName] lights up as Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName]'s plan finally comes to fruition.\n\nThe robots activate and immediately move with purpose. The crew of the [From.GetName] stare in shock, but warrantedly so, as the machines move out across the world, starting to cleanse the toxicity from it.\n\nOne could assume that the previous inhabitants were too wrapped up in conflict to save themselves."
CN2 anomaly.4106.desc:0 " [From.From.From.GetName] 上的那座设施因为科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 的努力而恢复运作了。\n\n机器人们启动后马上各就各位工作。 [From.GetName] 的船员们目瞪口呆，看着机器人们向四面八方移动，开始清除整个星球上的毒素。\n\n不禁让人猜测之前的种群是不是因为过于忙着自相残杀而忽略了自救。"
ADD anomaly.4106.desc.mach:0 "The facility on [From.From.From.GetName] lights up as Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName]'s plan comes to fruition.\n\nThe robots activate and immediately move with purpose. The crew units of the [From.GetName] observe as the ancient robots move out across the world, starting to cleanse the toxicity from it.\n\nOne could assume that the previous inhabitants were too wrapped up in petty conflict to save themselves. How typical of organics."
CN2 anomaly.4106.desc.mach:0 "当科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 的计划实现之时， [From.From.From.GetName] 上的设施也动了起来。\n\n机器人们被激活并立即开始工作。 [From.GetName] 的船员们目睹着远古机器人们横穿整个世界，开始净化上面的毒素。\n\n我们可以得出结论，这颗星球之前的居民忙于陷入冲突而无暇顾及自救。正是有机体一贯的作风。"
ADD anomaly.4106.a.tooltip:1 "The §YPlanet Class§! of [From.From.From.GetName] changes to §GContinental§!.\n\nAdds the §YFallen Robotic Society§! modifier to [From.From.From.GetName]:\n£engineering£ §G+3§!\n£building£ Robotic Assembly Plant §G+1§!\n£blocker£ Craters §R+2§!\n£blocker£ City Ruins §R+3§!"
CN2 anomaly.4106.a.tooltip:1 " [From.From.From.GetName] 的§Y行星类别§!更改为§G大陆§!。\n\n添加§Y失落的机械社会§!修正到 [From.From.From.GetName] ：\n£engineering §G+3§!\n£building 机器人组装工厂 §G+1§!\n£blocker 坑 §R+2§!\n£blocker 城市废墟 §R+3§!"
ADD anomaly.4106.b.tooltip:1 "Gives access to the §Y$edict_renewable_energy$§! Empire Edict.\n\nThe §YPlanet Class§! of [From.From.From.GetName] changes to §GContinental§!.\n\nAdds the §YFallen Robotic Society§! modifier to [From.From.From.GetName]:\n£engineering£ §G+3§!\n£building£ Robotic Assembly Plant §G+1§!\n£blocker£ Craters §R+2§!\n£blocker£ City Ruins §R+3§!"
CN2 anomaly.4106.b.tooltip:1 "解锁§Y$edict_renewable_energy$§!帝国法令。\n\n [From.From.From.GetName] 的§Y行星类别§!更改为§G大陆§!。\n\n添加§Y失落的机械社会§!修正到 [From.From.From.GetName] ：\n£engineering §G+3§!\n£building 机器人组装工厂 §G+1§!\n£blocker 坑 §R+2§!\n£blocker 城市废墟 §R+3§!"
ADD anomaly.4110.name:0 "Shifting Sands"
CN2 anomaly.4110.name:0 "沙上前行"
ADD anomaly.4110.success.desc:0 "The sand dunes of [From.GetName] are treacherous indeed. The fine grained sand runs almost like a liquid, making most landings an ordeal beyond measure.\n\nHowever, our brilliant science team has found a solution thanks to some innovative thinking. A chemical solution, fabricated by Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName], can be used to bind the sand in key locations, making the [From.GetPlanetMoon] easier to traverse."
CN2 anomaly.4110.success.desc:0 " [From.GetName] 的沙丘危险重重。那些光滑细腻的细沙就像液体般，对着陆造成了不可估量的困难。\n\n不过，我们机智的科学团队想到了一个创新的方法。由科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 配制的一种化学溶剂可以凝固关键地点的沙堆，让 [From.GetPlanetMoon] 更易于合勘测。"
ADD anomaly.4110.fail.desc:0 "The sand dunes of [From.GetName] are treachearous indeed. The sand is so finely grained that it almost could be called a liquid, and it swallows anything that sets down upon it. Settling here would take a heavy toll on personnel as well as structures.\n\nWith time we could probably learn how to work around these conditions. As the saying went: "Eventually our castle would stand upon the old one.""
CN2 anomaly.4110.fail.desc:0 " [From.GetName] 的沙丘危险重重。那些光滑细腻的细沙就像液体般，谁踏上去都会沉进沙里。在这里定居无疑会对人员及设施造成极大负担。\n\n也许假以时日，我们会克服这些难题。老话说得好：“长江后浪推前浪。”"
ADD anomaly.4110.a.tooltip:1 "Adds the §YLiquid Sands§! modifier to [From.GetName]:\nPhysics Research §G+6§!\n£blocker£ Quicksand Basin §R+5§!"
CN2 anomaly.4110.a.tooltip:1 "添加§Y流沙§!修正到 [From.GetName] ：\n物理学研究§G+6§!\n£blocker流沙盆地§R+5§!"
ADD anomaly.4110.b.tooltip:1 "Adds the §YShifting Sands§! and §YLiquid Sands§! modifier to [From.GetName]:\n£physics£ §G+3§!\n£blocker£ Quicksand Basin §R+7§!"
CN2 anomaly.4110.b.tooltip:1 "添加§Y移动的沙§!和§Y流沙§!修正到 [From.GetName] ：\n£physics §G+3§!\n£blocker 流沙盆地 §R+7§!"
ADD anomaly.4115.name:0 "Lurking in the Dark"
CN2 anomaly.4115.name:0 "暗中蛰伏"
ADD anomaly.4115.desc:0 "Catastrophe has struck the [Root.GetName]! After conducting their studies, with no interesting finds, the crew returned to the ship only to find it carrying a beast from the [From.GetPlanetMoon]! \n\nThe creature has already killed a crew member and is trying to claw itself through the walls to get to the others. They won't last long at this rate! A §SSpecial Project§! has been issued to save the ship."
CN2 anomaly.4115.desc:0 " [Root.GetName] 出大事了！研究结束后并无重大发现，船员便返回到船上，却发现 [From.GetPlanetMoon] 的某只猛兽竟然跑上了船！\n\n该生物已经消灭了一位船员，并正在撕毁墙壁试图逼近其他的船员们。他们撑不了多久！已经发布一个§S特殊项目§!去救人了。"
ADD anomaly.4115.desc.mach:0 "Catastrophe has struck the [Root.GetName]! After conducting their studies, with no interesting finds, the crew returned to the ship only to find it carrying an organic beast from the [From.GetPlanetMoon]! \n\nThe creature has already rendered one crew member unit inoperable, and is trying to claw itself through the walls to get to the others. They won't last long at this rate! A §SSpecial Project§! has been issued to save the ship."
CN2 anomaly.4115.desc.mach:0 " [Root.GetName] 发生了大灾难！在进行研究而一无所获之后，船员们返回飞船时却发现上面有一只来自 [From.GetPlanetMoon] 的有机体猛兽！\n\n这只猛兽已经瘫痪了一个船员单位，并正在试图用爪子割穿墙壁来干掉其他船员。这样下去他们活不长了！已下达一项§S特殊项目§!来拯救这艘飞船。"
ADD anomaly.4115.a:0 "Assemble a rescue force!"
CN2 anomaly.4115.a:0 "快组织救援队！"
ADD anomaly.4115.b:0 "Leave them to their fate."
CN2 anomaly.4115.b:0 "让他们听天由命吧。"
ADD anomaly.4115.b.tooltip:0 "The §Y[Root.GetName]§! is destroyed."
CN2 anomaly.4115.b.tooltip:0 "§Y [Root.GetName] §!被摧毁了。"
ADD anomaly.4116.desc:0 "Our rescue force has been successful in gunning down the beast aboard the [From.From.GetName]. Science Officer [From.From.GetLeaderName] and the team are rather traumatized, but assure that they are still fit for duty. Their appreciation of the soldiers saving them goes viral and we can already see a boost in new enlistees."
CN2 anomaly.4116.desc:0 "我们的救援队成功击毙了 [From.From.GetName] 上的那只猛兽。科研专员 [From.From.GetLeaderName] 和船员们都受到了惊吓，但依然能够胜任各自的职务。他们非常感激士兵们的援救，这件事激发了人们加入军团的热情。"
ADD anomaly.4116.desc.mach:0 "Our rescue force has been successful in gunning down the beast aboard the [From.From.GetName]. Science Officer [From.From.GetLeaderName] and the team have sustained negligable damage, and are still fit for duty. The success of our armed units in dispatching the organic menace has roused renewed focus among the assembly yards responsible for their construction.\n\nAs a result, we are noting an increase in combat unit build-speed and motivation software effectuality."
CN2 anomaly.4116.desc.mach:0 "我们的救援队成功地消灭了 [From.From.GetName] 上的猛兽。科研专员 [From.From.GetLeaderName] 及其团队只受到了轻微的损伤，并仍可执行任务。我们的战斗单位成功消灭了有机体威胁，使得建造他们的组装厂重新引起了注意。\n\n因此，我们的战斗单位建造速度以及积极性软件的有效性已有所提高。"
ADD anomaly.4116.a:0 "A proud day for the navy!"
CN2 anomaly.4116.a:0 "这是舰队的骄傲！"
ADD anomaly.4116.a.tooltip:1 "§YYour Empire§! gains the §G$army_inspiration$§! modifier."
CN2 anomaly.4116.a.tooltip:1 "§Y帝国§!获得了§G$army_inspiration$§!修正。"
ADD anomaly.4116.a.mach.tooltip:0 "§YYour Empire§! gains the §G$army_inspiration_mach$§! modifier."
CN2 anomaly.4116.a.mach.tooltip:0 "§Y帝国§!获得§G$army_inspiration_mach$§!修正。"
ADD anomaly.4117.desc:0 "Our rescue force has been successful in gunning down the beast aboard the [From.From.GetName]. Sadly they didn't make it in time to save Science Officer [From.From.GetLeaderName] who died while trying to protect the crew.\n\nAt least the ship is intact and the crew says they can go back to work soon. Our homeworld becomes abuzz about our military's bravery in handling the situation."
CN2 anomaly.4117.desc:0 "我们的救援队成功击毙了 [From.From.GetName] 上的那只猛兽。可惜他们没能及时拯救科研专员 [From.From.GetLeaderName] ，后者为了保护船员们而阵亡了。\n\n至少飞船无损，船员们很快就可以恢复工作。我们的母星沸腾了，都为我们的士兵们的英勇行为点赞。"
ADD anomaly.4117.desc.mach:0 "Our rescue force has been successful in gunning down the beast aboard the [From.From.GetName]. Unfortunately, they didn't make it in time to save Science Officer [From.From.GetLeaderName], who took terminal damage while trying to protect the crew units.\n\nAt least the ship is intact and the crew informs us they can resume normal functions soon. Our homeworld's circuits are abuzz with updates on our military's efficacy in handling the situation."
CN2 anomaly.4117.desc.mach:0 "我们的救援队成功地消灭了 [From.From.GetName] 上的猛兽。不幸的是，他们未能及时拯救试图保护船员而受到了致命损伤的科研专员 [From.From.GetLeaderName] 。\n\n至少飞船仍完好，并且船员们表示他们很快就能恢复行动。我们母星上的电路正忙着升级战斗单位在处理这种情况时的效率。"
ADD anomaly.4117.a.tooltip:0 "Lose the ship's §RScience Leader§!.\n§YYour Empire§! gains the §G$army_inspiration$§! modifier."
CN2 anomaly.4117.a.tooltip:0 "失去飞船的§R科学领队§!。§Y帝国§!获得了§G$army_inspiration$§!的修正。"
ADD anomaly.4117.a.mach.tooltip:0 "Lose the ship's §RScience Leader§!.\n§YYour Empire§! gains the §G$army_inspiration_mach$§! modifier."
CN2 anomaly.4117.a.mach.tooltip:0 "失去飞船的§R科学领袖§!。\n§Y帝国§!获得§G$army_inspiration_mach$§!修正。"
ADD anomaly.4120.name:0 "Explosions in the Sky"
CN2 anomaly.4120.name:0 "天空一道巨响"
ADD anomaly.4120.desc:0 "The [From.GetPlanetMoon] [From.GetName] is the home of a marvel of nature. Giant colorful explosions appear in the sky, a result of the chemical composition of the atmosphere reacting to the sun's gamma rays.\n\nStudents and senior scientists alike are spreading this find like a wildfire. It has generated quite the spark of interest for the scientific field amongst our people."
CN2 anomaly.4120.desc:0 " [From.GetPlanetMoon]  [From.GetName] 盛产大自然的奇迹。巨大的七彩爆炸出现在空中，这是因为大气层中的化学成分跟太阳的伽马射线产生了化学作用。\n\n学生们和高级科学家们都在传播着这个消息，消息如野火般扩散开来。科学领域中的相关人员都对此产生了兴趣。"
ADD anomaly.4125.name:0 "Lights Out in the Mines"
CN2 anomaly.4125.name:0 "熄灯的开采站"
ADD anomaly.4125.desc:1 "We have found an old mining station around the [From.GetPlanetMoon] [From.GetName], drifting in orbit. It was surely used to mine the planet of its resources, but by whom remains a mystery.\n\nThe technology within the station is very close to our own. We should be able to take hold of the station and have it up and running in no time. Or we could always scrap it for parts."
CN2 anomaly.4125.desc:1 "我们在 [From.GetPlanetMoon]  [From.GetName] 的轨道中发现了一个漂浮着的旧开采站。可以确定它是用于开采行星资源的，但是主人是谁就是个迷了。\n\n开采站的科技水平跟我们很相似。我们应该很快能修复好它并让它重新运作。或者也可以拆毁它获取零件。"
ADD anomaly.4125.a:0 "Take control of the station."
CN2 anomaly.4125.a:0 "接管开采站。"
ADD anomaly.4125.zerog.desc:0 "$anomaly.4125.desc$\n\nScience Officer [Root.GetLeaderName]'s superior knowledge of zero-g structures has helped us understand the inner workings of the station, allowing us to improve on our own designs."
CN2 anomaly.4125.zerog.desc:0 "$anomaly.4125.desc$\n\n科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 对于零重力建筑的博学多才让我们明白了开采站的内部构造，并且有助于改善我自己的设计。"
ADD anomaly.4125.a.tooltip:1 "Adds the §YAbandoned Mining Facility§! modifier to [From.GetName]:\nGain a §YMining Station§!\n£energy£ §G+3§!"
CN2 anomaly.4125.a.tooltip:1 "添加§Y被遗弃的开采站§!修正到 [From.GetName] ：\n获得一个§Y开采站§!\n£energy §G+3§!"
ADD anomaly.4125.b.tooltip:1 "§YYour Empire§! gains the §GZero-G Innovations§! modifier.\n\nAdds the §YAbandoned Mining Facility§! modifier to [From.GetName]:\nGain a §YMining Station§!\n£energy£ §G+3§!"
CN2 anomaly.4125.b.tooltip:1 "§Y帝国§!获得了§G零重力创新§!修正。\n\n添加§Y被遗弃的开采站§!修正到 [From.GetName] ：\n获得一个§Y开采站§!\n£energy §G+3§!"
ADD anomaly.4130.name:0 "The Tree"
CN2 anomaly.4130.name:0 "大树"
ADD anomaly.4130.desc:0 "Among the asteroids around [From.GetName] a tree is a drifting through the emptiness of space. An unprecedented and highly unlikely event! The tree is surrounded in a protective bubble, reminiscent of an energy shield.\n\nSuddenly we detect some hostile space dwellers on approach! This coincided with some sap leaking through the trees shield while we collected samples. Could it have agitated the creatures?"
CN2 anomaly.4130.desc:0 "在 [From.GetName] 周围的小行星带，一棵大树在空旷的太空中漂浮着。这样空前未有的事情真是说出来谁都不敢信！大树被一个保护层般的泡泡包围着，看上去像个能源护盾。\n\n我们突然检测到敌对的太空种群正在接近！这恰巧发生在我们采集样本并有树液从护盾中流出来的时候，难道它们是被这东西吸引过来的？"
ADD anomaly.4130.a:0 "We need to figure out what is going on!"
CN2 anomaly.4130.a:0 "我们得查出到底发生什么事了！"
ADD anomaly.4131.desc:0 "After rigorous research we now understand why the tree's sap summoned those creatures. The tree is able to produce a highly nutritious substance, which has machine-like abilities to repair organic tissue. The tree is a tree of life!\n\nIf we harvested it we could use it to expand the lifespan of our people. But there is one problem: the tree's healing power is limited in amount. We could only use it to improve a small group of peoples' life substantially, or increase everyone's situation by a small amount."
CN2 anomaly.4131.desc:0 "经过仔细的研究我们终于明白为什么树液会把那些生物吸引过来了。这棵树会生产一种非常高营养价值的液体，可以修复细胞组织。这简直是生命之树啊！\n\n如果我们可以采集这东西，我们就能够延长人们的寿命。但问题是：大树就一棵而已，我们要么大幅提升一小群人的寿命，要么小幅提升所有人的寿命。"
ADD anomaly.4131.a:0 "Give it to our leaders."
CN2 anomaly.4131.a:0 "拿去给领袖享用。"
ADD anomaly.4131.b:0 "Give it to the people."
CN2 anomaly.4131.b:0 "人人平等，大家一起用。"
ADD anomaly.4131.c:0 "Let the tree drift along."
CN2 anomaly.4131.c:0 "让大树继续飘啊飘。"
ADD anomaly.4135.name:0 "Teachings of Settlers"
CN2 anomaly.4135.name:0 "殖民者的教诲"
ADD anomaly.4135.desc:1 "On [From.GetName] the crew of the [Root.GetName] have found something extraordinary. The planet's dunes have hid several ruins, belonging to an interstellar civilization of settlers. The settlements have long been destroyed by the ravages of time.\n\nScience Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] is quick to discover a stored cache of valuables and documents. The collection of texts must have been most revered by the settlers, as they were stored amongst other valuables."
CN2 anomaly.4135.desc:1 " [Root.GetName] 的船员在 [From.GetName] 上有重大发现。该行星上的沙丘隐藏着一些废墟，是属于一个星际种群的。这类殖民地大都敌不过时间的洗礼。\n\n科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 很快发现了一个藏有珍贵物品和文件的储物箱。既然这些文件是跟珍贵物品保存在一起，那一定相当重要。"
ADD anomaly.4135.b:1 "Sell it to a private collector."
CN2 anomaly.4135.b:1 "卖给私人收藏家。"
ADD anomaly.4136.desc:0 "Having had our linguistics experts hard at work for months, we've finally succeeded in translating the works found on [From.From.From.GetName].The papers are the teachings of an alien scholar only referred to as "Telisa the Teller of Tales." All mentions of her points to her being a famous philosopher and overall expert on society and relations.\n\n$anomaly.4136.base.desc$"
CN2 anomaly.4136.desc:0 "我们的语言专家废寝忘食数个月，终于成功翻译了 [From.From.From.GetName] 上找到的文献。这些文件是一位被称为说书人特丽莎的著作。她似乎是位非常有名的哲学家、社会学家、关系学家。\n\n$anomaly.4136.base.desc$"
ADD anomaly.4136.found.desc:0 "It seems that the text we found on [From.From.From.GetName] is another piece created by "Telisa the Teller of Tales."$anomaly.4136.base.desc$"
CN2 anomaly.4136.found.desc:0 " [From.From.From.GetName] 上发现的文件似乎也是说书人特丽莎的著作。$anomaly.4136.base.desc$"
ADD anomaly.4136.base.desc:0 "The documents explicitly details how you can refocus infrastructure and shape society. She meant that by having everyone sacrifice some of their comfort for the greater good the nation will flourish."
CN2 anomaly.4136.base.desc:0 "这些文件详细地解释如何重整基础设施和塑造社会。她的意思是所有人都牺牲自己的一部分幸福，为帝国共创美好的未来。"
ADD anomaly.4136.a.tooltip:0 "Gives access to the §Y$edict_masters_writings_politics$§! Empire Edict."
CN2 anomaly.4136.a.tooltip:0 "可以使用§Y$edict_masters_writings_politics$§!的帝国法令。"
ADD anomaly.4140.name:0 "Teachings of Explorers"
CN2 anomaly.4140.name:0 "探索者的教诲"
ADD anomaly.4140.desc:0 "The [Root.GetName]'s crew is reporting that they've found something spectacular on [From.GetName]. On the surface lies traces of an explorative expedition of another civilization. Left behind are some well-preserved documents and artifacts.\n\nThe proposed action by chief Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] is to send the text findings to our homeworld for translation. There is also the possibility to sell them off to a private investor."
CN2 anomaly.4140.desc:0 " [Root.GetName] 的船员发来报告称，他们在 [From.GetName] 上找到了惊人的发现。其他文明的探索队在其表面留下了痕迹，并遗留了一些保存完好的档案及文物。\n\n首席科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 提议将文献送回母星破译。但也可以将其卖给私人投资者。"
ADD anomaly.4141.desc:0 "After many weeks of study, our expert linguists have unearthed the meaning behind the documents found on [From.From.From.GetName]. The documents were philosophical ponderings by a famous scholar, only referred to as "Telisa the Teller of Tales."\n\n$anomaly.4141.base.desc$"
CN2 anomaly.4141.desc:0 "通过数周的研究，我们的语言学专家破解了 [From.From.From.GetName] 的文档中包含的内容。该文档记录了一位知名学者的哲学思辨，她被称为“说书人特丽莎”。\n\n$anomaly.4141.base.desc$"
ADD anomaly.4141.found.desc:0 "Who would've thought? The texts we found were more teachings from "Telisa the Teller of Tales." This time it's a collection of philosophical ponderings and analysis on larger questions.\n\n$anomaly.4141.base.desc$"
CN2 anomaly.4141.found.desc:0 "谁能想到呢？我们发现的文献记录了更多“说书人特丽莎”的教诲。这次，是一些对更宏观问题的哲思与分析。\n\n$anomaly.4141.base.desc$"
ADD anomaly.4141.base.desc:0 "Her teachings have provided us with much insight into how to better gain political results via applying different states of mind and use larger scale questions as a focus for reform."
CN2 anomaly.4141.base.desc:0 "她的教诲让我们对治理帝国有了更加深刻的理解，通过应用不同的看法，并在革命时关注宏观问题，可以获得更好的治理成果。"
ADD anomaly.4141.a.tooltip:0 "Gives access to the §Y$edict_masters_writings_philosophy$§! Empire Edict."
CN2 anomaly.4141.a.tooltip:0 "可以使用§Y$edict_masters_writings_philosophy$§!的帝国法令。"
ADD anomaly.4145.name:0 "The Slavers' Downfall"
CN2 anomaly.4145.name:0 "奴隶主的毁灭"
ADD anomaly.4145.base.desc:0 "On [From.GetName] the nuclear winter is far from over. Nothing alive remains on any part of the planet. Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] reports the team's findings: Everything points towards a civil war having broken out within a previously unified civilization.\n\nThe root cause of the war was most likely the conflict between different stewards who all wanted control over larger parts of the union's slaves."
CN2 anomaly.4145.base.desc:0 " [From.GetName] 上的核冬天还会持续很久。整个行星都没有生物存活。科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 汇报了队伍的调查结果：一切证据都指明，这里曾存在统一的文明，但陷入了争斗。\n\n战争的起因可能是一些小族长成为争夺帝国更大的奴隶控制权产生了矛盾。"
ADD anomaly.4145.desc:0 "$anomaly.4145.base.desc$\n\nThankfully we're not close to this happening to us, but we should let it stand as a testament to the lunacy of slavery."
CN2 anomaly.4145.desc:0 "$anomaly.4145.base.desc$\n\n所幸，我们的历史上没有发生这种事，但我们可以从中获得警示，施行奴隶制是一种愚傻的行为。"
ADD anomaly.4145.slaver.desc:0 "$anomaly.4145.base.desc$\n\nThis does not help our own way of life appear in any sort of favorable light."
CN2 anomaly.4145.slaver.desc:0 "$anomaly.4145.base.desc$\n\n这些发现对我们的生活方式毫无帮助。"
ADD anomaly.4145.soon.desc:0 "$anomaly.4145.base.desc$\n\nWe should think twice before treading the same path."
CN2 anomaly.4145.soon.desc:0 "$anomaly.4145.base.desc$\n\n我们必须谨慎，免得步入后尘。"
ADD anomaly.4145.a:0 "The folly of slavers..."
CN2 anomaly.4145.a:0 "愚傻的奴隶主……"
ADD anomaly.4145.b:0 "One starts to wonder..."
CN2 anomaly.4145.b:0 "真让人吃惊……"
ADD anomaly.4145.a.tooltip:0 "§YYour Empire§! gains the §R$slavery_bad_juju$§! modifier.\n\n"
CN2 anomaly.4145.a.tooltip:0 "§Y帝国§!获得了§R$slavery_bad_juju$§!修正。"
ADD anomaly.4145.b.tooltip:0 "§YYour Empire§! gains the §R$slavery_very_bad_juju$§! modifier.\n\n"
CN2 anomaly.4145.b.tooltip:0 "§Y帝国§!获得了§R$slavery_very_bad_juju$§!修正。"
ADD anomaly.4150.name:0 "Teachings of Traders"
CN2 anomaly.4150.name:0 "贸易商的教诲"
ADD anomaly.4150.desc:0 "The surface of [From.GetName] holds something remarkable. Multiple ruins can be found, built using different architectures, yet from the same point in history. The [From.GetPlanetMoon] might have been a trading hub!\n\nSome ruins held stored documents and valuables. If we studied the texts we might be able to translate them and learn more about the people who settled here. Or we could sell them to someone who values old heirlooms."
CN2 anomaly.4150.desc:0 " [From.GetName] 的表面屹立着值得注意的建筑群。这些遗迹拥有不同的建筑风格，但都建于同一时代。 [From.GetPlanetMoon] 曾经可能是一个交易中心。\n\n某些遗迹中存有文档和财物。我们可以通过研究文本来尝试翻译，以便了解曾定居在这里的生物。我们也可以将其卖给古董收藏家。"
ADD anomaly.4151.desc:0 "Our most talented linguists have been hard at work in translating the documents we found on [From.From.From.GetName]. The scribe behind these works is referred to as "Telisa the Teller of Tales," and it seems she was highly revered during her time.\n\n$anomaly.4151.base.desc$"
CN2 anomaly.4151.desc:0 "我们天才的语言学专家正在努力翻译 [From.From.From.GetName] 上发现的文献。文献的作者被称作“说书人特丽莎”，似乎是当时的德高望重之人。\n\n$anomaly.4151.base.desc$"
ADD anomaly.4151.found.desc:0 "Who would've thought? The texts we found were more teachings from "Telisa the Teller of Tales."\n\n$anomaly.4151.base.desc$"
CN2 anomaly.4151.found.desc:0 "谁能想到呢？我们发现的文献记录了更多“说书人特丽莎”的教诲。\n\n$anomaly.4151.base.desc$"
ADD anomaly.4151.base.desc:0 "The documents we found were a collection of anecdotes, suggestions and techniques for how to optimally partake in interstellar diplomacy. She seemed to have believed that good trade and respectful communication would achieve great social advancements for all parties."
CN2 anomaly.4151.base.desc:0 "这份文档记录了一些奇闻趣事、如何从星际外交中获取最大利益的建议和技巧。她相信，公平贸易和互相尊重的沟通可以为各界带来巨大的社会进步。"
ADD anomaly.4151.a.tooltip:0 "Gives access to the §Y$edict_masters_writings_diplomacy$§! Empire Edict."
CN2 anomaly.4151.a.tooltip:0 "可以使用§Y$edict_masters_writings_diplomacy$§!的帝国法令。"
ADD anomaly.4155.name:0 "Beneath the Battlefield"
CN2 anomaly.4155.name:0 "战场之下"
ADD anomaly.4155.desc:0 "[From.GetName] used to hold an advanced civilization. It is now dead silent. Alien beasts roam old battlefields that stretch across the surface.\n\nIn a rocky region there seems to lie a hidden vault beneath the mountains. If we could get rid of the beasts roaming the landscape we could investigate it."
CN2 anomaly.4155.desc:0 " [From.GetName] 曾经拥有一个高等文明。但他们早已成为历史尘埃。异形猛兽在星球表面的远古战场上肆虐横行。\n\n在石山地区的山脉底部藏有一个避难所。如果我们能先处理掉地表的猛兽，我们就可以继续调查。"
ADD anomaly.4155.a:0 "Let's try and get to it!"
CN2 anomaly.4155.a:0 "马上动手尝试！"
ADD anomaly.4155.b:0 "Leave the vault, and its wandering spirits be."
CN2 anomaly.4155.b:0 "远离避难所和在那里游荡的灵魂。"
ADD anomaly.4156.desc:0 "With the beasts removed, we could access the vault. Inside it lay a headquarter of sorts, a last refuge for a dying world's leaders.\n\nThe vault is filled with destroyed equipment and decomposed corpses. The only thing of interest being a container, which potentially holds something of importance."
CN2 anomaly.4156.desc:0 "清除猛兽后，我们进入了避难所。内部似乎是一间指挥室，为这个死亡文明的领袖们提供最后的庇护。\n\n避难所内全是破损的设备和腐烂的尸体。唯一值得调查的是一个容器，可能装有十分重要的东西。"
ADD anomaly.4156.b:0 "Only study the vault to avoid risks."
CN2 anomaly.4156.b:0 "以防万一，只研究避难所。"
ADD anomaly.4157.name:0 "Cryopod Warrior"
CN2 anomaly.4157.name:0 "冷冻舱中的勇士"
ADD anomaly.4157.desc:0 "The container found on [WarriorHomePlanet.GetName] turned out to be a cryogenic device! The preserved alien within has awoken. She speaks using telepathic concepts:\n\n"Why have you brought me back, captor? Is the war of my people over?""
CN2 anomaly.4157.desc:0 "在 [WarriorHomePlanet.GetName] 上发现的容器原来是一个冷藏装置！封存的外星人已经苏醒。她用心灵感应说道：\n\n“为什么叫醒我？我们种群的战争结束了吗？”"
ADD anomaly.4157.a:0 "You are on [HomePlanet.GetName]. You are safe here."
CN2 anomaly.4157.a:0 "你目前在 [HomePlanet.GetName] 上。这里很安全。"
ADD anomaly.4157.b:0 "Your home planet was ruined by the war, only you remain."
CN2 anomaly.4157.b:0 "你的家乡被战争毁灭了，只有你幸存。"
ADD anomaly.4157.c:0 "We salvaged what we could of your ruined homeworld."
CN2 anomaly.4157.c:0 "我们尽力从你们被毁的家园抢救物资。"
ADD anomaly.4158.desc:0 ""I feared that this would happen. I only hope that my knowledge, and our failure as a species, can teach others.""
CN2 anomaly.4158.desc:0 "“我就怕这种事发生。希望我的知识和我们种群的悲剧能带给别人教诲。”"
ADD anomaly.4159.desc:0 ""So that's why... I feared that I would wake up to these news. To be honest I feared I would never wake at all. What does your kind want of me?""
CN2 anomaly.4159.desc:0 "“是这样吗……我就怕醒来时会得到这个消息。说实话，我更怕永远醒不过来。你们种群想从我这里获得什么？”"
ADD anomaly.4158.a:0 "Tell us about yourself."
CN2 anomaly.4158.a:0 "说说你自己。"
ADD anomaly.4158.a.response:0 ""I am Majula, the one bearing the title of "The Bearer." I was a general, advisor to the Queen of the East, and her loyal friend.""
CN2 anomaly.4158.a.response:0 "“我叫玛居拉，拥有“领受者”的称号。我是一名将军，是东方女王的顾问，也是她忠诚的朋友。”"
ADD anomaly.4158.b:0 "Why were you preserved?"
CN2 anomaly.4158.b:0 "为什么你被冷藏了？"
ADD anomaly.4158.spiritual.b:0 "Where you frozen to carry a divine mission?"
CN2 anomaly.4158.spiritual.b:0 "被冷藏的你是有什么使命吗？"
ADD anomaly.4158.militant.b:0 "To be frozen in war you must be of high value?"
CN2 anomaly.4158.militant.b:0 "在战时被冷冻，你一定是个重要人物？"
ADD anomaly.4158.b.response:0 ""I bore the title of "The Bearer." I was responsible of representing our people, would we end up walking the path of extinction. My knowledge of war was only outranked by my knowledge of our people.""
CN2 anomaly.4158.b.response:0 "“我拥有‘领受者’的称号。如果我们走向了灭亡，我要负责代表我的人民。除了对自己种群的了解，我在战争方面的知识最为丰富。”"
ADD anomaly.4158.c:0 "Tell us about your people."
CN2 anomaly.4158.c:0 "说说你的人民。"
ADD anomaly.4158.c.response:0 ""A troubled kind. Our history is... was filled with stories of our inability to steer clear from the road to destruction. The group was unable to live up to the potential of the individual. We had many wise speakers, but few who chose to listen.""
CN2 anomaly.4158.c.response:0 "“惹是生非的种群。我们的历史中……走向毁灭之路的故事比比皆是。人们不懂得实现自身价值。虽然存在许多明智之人，但很少有人愿意倾听。”"
ADD anomaly.4158.d:0 "Will you join us?"
CN2 anomaly.4158.d:0 "你会加入我们吗？"
ADD anomaly.4158.f:0 "Leave. Your fate is your own."
CN2 anomaly.4158.f:0 "离开吧。你的命运由你自己掌控。"
ADD anomaly.4158.xenophobe.f:0 "You are of no use to us. Leave our planet!"
CN2 anomaly.4158.xenophobe.f:0 "你没有利用价值。离开我们的星球！"
ADD anomaly.4160.desc:0 ""Your words, and your civilization speaks to me, captor. I will join you, in hopes that you will learn from my people's mistakes."
CN2 anomaly.4160.desc:0 "“你的话语和你的文明向我证明了一切，捕获者。我会加入你，希望你能吸取我们种群的教训。”"
ADD anomaly.4161.desc:0 "The way you speak. The way this room speaks for you. It tells me that our views do not align, captor. So no, I will not join you. I will return to [WarriorHomePlanet.GetName], and tell its stories for as long as I remain.""
CN2 anomaly.4161.desc:0 "你的话语，还有这个房间的氛围，都证明了我们的观点不合。所以我不会加入你。我会回到 [WarriorHomePlanet.GetName] ，穷尽一生讲述它的故事。"
ADD anomaly.4161.a:0 "Then go in peace."
CN2 anomaly.4161.a:0 "那就静静地离开吧。"
ADD anomaly.4161.b:0 "Seize her!"
CN2 anomaly.4161.b:0 "抓住她！"
ADD anomaly.4162.desc:0 ""I would rather die!"\n\nMajula runs out of the room, enraged. As a crowd had gathered outside to take part in the proceedings she grabs a researcher to use as leverage. In the escape, the researcher dies before Majula is gunned down by security."
CN2 anomaly.4162.desc:0 "“宁死不屈！”\n\n玛居拉愤怒地冲出房间。外面的人群正准备进行阻拦，她就抓住了一名研究员作为人质。在逃离过程中，人质不幸牺牲而玛居拉也被警卫击毙。"
ADD anomaly.4163.desc:0 ""Farewell, captor. Try and learn from what happened to my people, lest we meet again and you too have ended up to be the last of your kind.""
CN2 anomaly.4163.desc:0 "“再见了，捕获者。试着吸取我们种群的教训，千万不要在我们下一次相遇时，你也成了你们种群的最后一人。”"
ADD anomaly.4163.a:0 "Farewell."
CN2 anomaly.4163.a:0 "再见了。"
ADD anomaly.4163.b:0 "Get out!"
CN2 anomaly.4163.b:0 "出去！"
ADD anomaly.4165.name:0 "Teachings of Warriors"
CN2 anomaly.4165.name:0 "勇士的教诲"
ADD anomaly.4165.desc:0 "Across the barren fields of [From.GetName] there are indications of old battles being fought. Beneath the lifeless ground our researchers on the [Root.GetName] have found bones, metallic shards and, most surprisingly, a container filled with documents.\n\nIf we send the documents to our homeworld for translation we could potentially learn more about this war and who fought in it. It would also be possible to simply sell them off as antiques."
CN2 anomaly.4165.desc:0 "在 [From.GetName] 的荒野上，发现了战斗过的痕迹。在毫无生机的地表下， [Root.GetName] 的研究员发现了骸骨和金属碎片，最令人吃惊的是一个装着文档的容器。\n\n如果我们将文档送回母星破译，我们有机会了解这场战争和参与战争的种群。但也可以直接将其卖给古董商。"
ADD anomaly.4166.desc:0 "Our language experts have been at it for weeks to try and translate the documents we found in the old battlefield. Today we finally have some results. We now know that the fallen warriors all followed the teachings of a philosopher called "Telisa the Teller of Tales."\n\n$anomaly.4166.base.desc$"
CN2 anomaly.4166.desc:0 "几周来，我们的语言学专家一直在破译远古战场留下的文档。今天研究有了一些进展。我们得知，倒下的勇士遵循的教义来自于一个叫“说书人特丽莎”的哲学家。\n\n$anomaly.4166.base.desc$"
ADD anomaly.4166.found.desc:0 "It appears that the texts we found buried in the battlefield were more teachings written by "Telisa the Teller of Tales."\n\n$anomaly.4166.base.desc$"
CN2 anomaly.4166.found.desc:0 "我们从战场上挖掘到的文献上记录了更多“说书人特丽莎”的教诲。\n\n$anomaly.4166.base.desc$"
ADD anomaly.4166.base.desc:0 "The documents are breakdowns of tactics, strategy and, most importantly, logistics in interstellar warfare. Being a strong spokesperson against war, Telisa still found this to be essential knowledge for steering into the future. "Even the most peaceful of people might be forced into a corner in their work for a better world.""
CN2 anomaly.4166.base.desc:0 "这个文档对各种战术、战略进行了解析，最关键的是，其中包含星际战争的后勤学。特丽莎本人强烈反对战争，但她认为这种知识在未来时代仍然十分重要。“为了创建更美好的世界，即便是最和平的种群，也会有被逼迫到死角的时候。”"
ADD anomaly.4166.a:0 "Even the wise can go to war it seems."
CN2 anomaly.4166.a:0 "看来智者也会选择战争。"
ADD anomaly.4166.a.tooltip:0 "Gives access to the §Y$edict_masters_writings_war$§! Empire Edict."
CN2 anomaly.4166.a.tooltip:0 "可以使用§Y$edict_masters_writings_war$§!的帝国法令。"
ADD anomaly.4170.name:0 "Volatile Resources"
CN2 anomaly.4170.name:0 "易燃性资源"
ADD anomaly.4170.start.desc:0 "Scans of the [From.GetPlanetMoon] has unveiled dense deposits of natural gases underneath the surface. The rich resource is extremely energy efficient and would greatly increase the energy output of our surface production."
CN2 anomaly.4170.start.desc:0 "扫描结果显示， [From.GetPlanetMoon] 的地表下拥有高浓度的天然气。这种丰厚的资源非常高效节能，可以大大增加地表设施的能源产出。"
ADD anomaly.4170.basic.desc:0 "$anomaly.4170.start.desc$\n\nHowever, using these resources would deplete them rather quickly, as the deposits are rare and small in size."
CN2 anomaly.4170.basic.desc:0 "$anomaly.4170.start.desc$\n\n然而，这些资源将会很快耗尽，因为储量稀少、体积较小。"
ADD anomaly.4170.material.desc:0 "$anomaly.4170.start.desc$\n\nThe potential gain this would serve to us because heavily outweighs any damage that could be caused to the environment."
CN2 anomaly.4170.material.desc:0 "$anomaly.4170.start.desc$\n\n它带来的好处远比对环境造成的破坏要大。"
ADD anomaly.4170.a:0 "Prepare to start digging!"
CN2 anomaly.4170.a:0 "准备进行开采！"
ADD anomaly.4170.a.tooltip:1 "Adds the §YRich Gas Deposits§! modifier to [From.GetName]:\n£energy£ §G+50%§!"
CN2 anomaly.4170.a.tooltip:1 " [From.GetName] 获得§Y丰富气藏§!的修正：\n£energy §G+50%§!"
ADD anomaly.4170.b:0 "Exploiting the planet is not a long-term solution."
CN2 anomaly.4170.b:0 "开采行星不是长久之计。"
ADD anomaly.4170.b.tooltip:1 "Adds the §YResponsible Gas Mining§! modifier to [From.GetName]:\n£energy£ §G+5§!"
CN2 anomaly.4170.b.tooltip:1 " [From.GetName] 获得§Y合理气体开采§!的修正：\n£energy §G+5§!"
ADD anomaly.4172.conqueror.desc:0 "The colony we took over used to hold rich resources of gas underneath the surface. Now they've depleted, reducing the energy output of our industries."
CN2 anomaly.4172.conqueror.desc:0 "我们占据的殖民地曾拥有丰富的地下气体资源。但现在已经耗尽，工厂的能源输出降低。"
ADD anomaly.4172.owner.desc:0 "The energy rich gas found on one of our colonies has now depleted. The extra resource output has been lost, greatly increasing our need for new deposits to replace it."
CN2 anomaly.4172.owner.desc:0 "富含能源的气体已经耗尽。这个殖民地已失去额外的资源输出，大大增加了我们对新矿藏的需求。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4000.desc:0 "[Root.GetLeaderName] has made a traumatizing discovery. The flora on [From.From.GetName] is extremely dangerous to non-plant organisms. We do not fully understand what is causing this; all we know is that large parts of the [From.From.GetPlanetMoon] is outright lethal and that this will restrict growth of potential settlements."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4000.desc:0 " [Root.GetLeaderName] 有了惊人发现。 [From.From.GetName] 的植被对非植物有机体极其危险。我们还不清楚其中原理；只知道 [From.From.GetPlanetMoon] 十分危险，这将限制其殖民地的发展。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4000.a:0 "This is truly a horrific place."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4000.a:0 "真是个可怕的地方。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4000.a.tooltip:1 "Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] gains the §RParanoid§! Trait.\n\nAdds the §YAcid Jungles§! modifier to [From.From.GetName]:\n£blocker£ Noxious Swamp §R+3§!\n£society£ §G+6§!"
CN2 anomaly_failure.4000.a.tooltip:1 "科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 获得§R偏执狂§!特性。\n\n [From.From.GetName] 获得§Y酸性丛林§!的修正：\n£blocker 剧毒沼泽 §R+3§!\n£society §G+6§!"
ADD anomaly_failure.4005.desc:0 "Unfortunately, our team has not been able to deduce anything of great interest from the asteroid, as first expected, except for some common minerals."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4005.desc:0 "很不幸，我们的科研队伍没能从小行星中发现任何有价值的东西，和当初预想的不同，只发现了一些普通矿物。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4005.a.tooltip:1 "Adds resources to [From.From.GetName]:\n£minerals£ §G+1§!"
CN2 anomaly_failure.4005.a.tooltip:1 " [From.From.GetName] 增添资源：\n£minerals §G+1§!"
ADD anomaly_failure.4010.desc:0 "Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] reports that after extensive probing and scanning of the [From.From.GetPlanetMoon], nothing of interest has been found."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4010.desc:0 "科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 汇报称，经过大范围探测和扫描后，并未在 [From.From.GetPlanetMoon] 上发现有价值的东西。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4011.desc:0 "Having searched the ship and inspected the crew's remains, Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] has deduced that the crewmembers must have killed each other. The solitude and confinement of space travel can break even the strongest of minds."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4011.desc:0 "在调查飞船和船员的残骸后，科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 推测船员们一定是自相残杀。太空旅行的孤独与禁闭甚至可以击溃最强大的意志。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4012.desc:0 "We are receiving a distress signal from the [Root.GetName]. The crew has gone mad and are killing each other! The captain has lost all control, sending help would be futile at this point. Could this have anything to do with that derelict ship they recently investigated?"
CN2 anomaly_failure.4012.desc:0 "我们从 [Root.GetName] 收到了求救信号。船员开始发疯地互相残杀！舰长已经失去控制，派船救援已经来不及了。这和他们刚刚调查的古船有关吗？"
ADD anomaly_failure.4012.a.tooltip:0 "The §Y[Root.GetName]§! is destroyed."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4012.a.tooltip:0 "§Y [Root.GetName] §!被摧毁了。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4015.desc:0 "The [Root.GetName]'s crew report that they have found nothing of interest."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4015.desc:0 " [Root.GetName] 的船员汇报称，他们没有发现有价值的东西。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4025.desc:0 "The science team of the [Root.GetName] reports that they have not found the impactful data they first expected [From.From.GetName] to hold."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4025.desc:0 " [Root.GetName] 的科研队伍汇报称，他们没能按预期找到 [From.From.GetName] 上的珍贵数据。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4030.desc:0 "Having combed the desert, we have not found anything of value!"
CN2 anomaly_failure.4030.desc:0 "翻遍了整个沙漠，我们也未能找到有价值的东西！"
ADD anomaly_failure.4031.desc:0 "We were unable to stall the fleet AI on [From.From.GetName]. Their ancient ships are taking to the skies and beyond, looking for the next battle according to their programmed parameters."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4031.desc:0 "我们未能阻止 [From.From.GetName] 上的飞舰载人工智能。他们的古船飞向遥远的天际，按照程序参数寻找下一个战场。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4031.a:0 "The rage of the machine is worth fearing."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4031.a:0 "机器的怒火值得恐惧。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4035.desc:0 "Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] reports that the radiation readings they so desperately wanted to examine were the result of a rare instrument malfunction. It has now been taken care of."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4035.desc:0 "科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 汇报称，他们苦心寻找的辐射是突发的设备异常所造成的读数错误。现在已经修理好了。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4037.desc:0 "The radiation readings indicate that this is not the solar system we were looking for."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4037.desc:0 "根据辐射读数，这不是我们要寻找的恒星系。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4037.a:0 "We have to keep looking."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4037.a:0 "我们必须继续调查。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4045.desc:0 "We simply cannot lock down what those subtle readings on [From.From.GetName] were. The team is frustrated and promise to improve."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4045.desc:0 "我们就是无法确定 [From.From.GetName] 上微弱读数的源头。失落的科研队表示会思过整改。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4055.desc:0 "The [Root.GetName] reports that they have been unable to find anything to deliver on the promised finds. Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] is distraught and apologizes for the mistake."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4055.desc:0 " [Root.GetName] 汇报称，他们未能找到原本承诺会找到的东西。科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 因此心烦意乱，并为失误道歉。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4055.a:0 "Do not worry, [Root.GetLeaderName]."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4055.a:0 "别担心， [Root.GetLeaderName] 。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4055.b:0 "Do not make any more mistakes."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4055.b:0 "不要再犯错了。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4060.desc:0 "After closer inspection, Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] only found random space debris orbiting the star. It probably originated from a nearby asteroid belt."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4060.desc:0 "经过仔细调查后，科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 只在恒星轨道上发现了普通的太空碎片。它们可能源自附近的小行星带。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4066.desc:0 "We could not stop the rampaging drill before it was too late. It dug too deep and was eventually crushed under the weight of rocky detritus of its own creation."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4066.desc:0 "一切都太迟了，我们未能阻止前进的钻头。它钻得太深，最后被重重的岩石压碎。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4070.desc:0 "Science Officer [Root.GetLeaderName] reports that the [From.From.GetPlanetMoon] [From.From.GetName] follows the patterns expected of a tropical [From.From.GetPlanetMoon]. The anomaly that was detected seems to have been a dud."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4070.desc:0 "科研专员 [Root.GetLeaderName] 汇报称， [From.From.GetPlanetMoon]  [From.From.GetName] 遵循的轨道与普通热带 [From.From.GetPlanetMoon] 的预计轨道相同。这次异常报告似乎是误报。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4071.desc:0 "Troublingly, we have found that [From.From.GetName] is very hostile, despite our initial scans pointing towards nothing of the sort. Potential colonizers would have to deal with terrible conditions, such as hazardous weathers, high temperatures and poisonous plants and wildlife."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4071.desc:0 "我们遇到了麻烦，和初步扫描结果不同， [From.From.GetName] 其实十分危险。对其殖民可能会遭遇不利情况，如灾害性天气、高温和毒性动植物。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4075.desc:0 "The harsh climate has taken its toll and our science team have failed to reveal anything about [From.From.GetName] that we did not already know."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4075.desc:0 "严峻的气候让我们损失惨重，研究小队没能发掘更多关于 [From.GetName] 的未知信息。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4080.desc:0 "The [From.From.GetPlanetMoon] seems to be less interesting than we had hoped. The readings pointing to previous settlements seem to have been triggered by oddly symmetrical mineral formations."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4080.desc:0 " [From.From.GetPlanetMoon] 似乎没有预想中的那么特别。先前的读数异常似乎是由偶然形成的对称矿脉造成的。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4081.desc:0 "Bad news from the repairs project on [From.From.From.GetName]. The construction workers have not been able to fix the broken machine, as it has started to break down even further and seems to be beyond repair."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4081.desc:0 " [From.From.From.GetName] 的修复工程传来坏消息。建筑工人未能修理坏掉的机器，机器开始自行解体，已经无法修理了。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4086.desc:0 "Sadly we were not able to save the drifting ship close to [From.From.From.GetName] before it was too late. An untracked asteroid appeared on a collision course and smashed the ship to pieces."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4086.desc:0 "很遗憾，未能抢救靠近 [From.From.From.GetName] 的漂流船。一个未侦测到的小行星突然出现在碰撞航向上，把那艘船撞成了碎片。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4086.military:0 "The cargo was more important."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4086.military:0 "上面的货物更重要。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4090.desc:0 "We lost the signal. It appears to have come from a ship, but suddenly it just vanished. It might have performed an FTL jump, or something much worse happened to it."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4090.desc:0 "我们丢失了信号。那个信号似乎是一艘飞船发出的，但突然就消失了。也许它进行了超光速跃迁，或者遭遇了更可怕的状况。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4090.a:0 "A new contact, lost to the void."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4090.a:0 "一次新的接触机会就这么丢失了。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4090.b:0 "Good. Alien interests are none of our concern."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4090.b:0 "很好。我们并不关心外星人。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4116.desc:0 "A last transmission has been received from the monster-infested ship. It tells us that the beast succeeded in getting through to the crew's hiding place.\n\nThe horrid encounter was far too graphic to describe. There were no survivors."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4116.desc:0 "被怪兽侵袭的飞船发来了最后的电报。那些野兽已经成功突破到了船员藏身的地方。\n\n情况太过残忍，就不多做描述了。没有生还者。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4116.a:0 "We failed them..."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4116.a:0 "我们辜负了他们……"
ADD anomaly_failure.4116.a.tooltip:0 "The §YScience Ship§! is destroyed."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4116.a.tooltip:0 "§Y科研船§!被摧毁。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4136.desc:0 "Sadly our linguists have been unable to understand the entirety of the alien language used in the old documents found on [From.From.From.GetName]. However, they managed to translate the essentials, which has given us a glimpse into the culture they originated from."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4136.desc:0 "十分可惜，我们的语言学家未能完全理解 [From.From.From.GetName] 上古老文献的外星语言。不过，他们翻译了一些核心内容，让我们得以窥探那个文明的文化。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4156.desc:0 "Fighting off the beasts around the underground vault on [WarriorHomePlanet.GetName] has caused the complex to collapse. We are unable to salvage anything of value from the debris."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4156.desc:0 "在 [WarriorHomePlanet.GetName] 的地下避难所附近清除野兽时，战斗意外地导致了建筑崩塌。我们未能从残骸中回收到有价值的东西。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4157.base:0 "Opening up the container we found on [WarriorHomePlanet.GetName] revealed it to hold samples of healthy crops, as well as instruments that would help it grow again in infertile conditions."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4157.base:0 "打开 [WarriorHomePlanet.GetName] 上发现的容器后，我们找到了一些健康作物的样本，还有一些辅助器材，这可以让样本在肥沃条件下重新生长。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4157.desc:0 "$anomaly_failure.4157.base$ We could reverse engineer this."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4157.desc:0 "$anomaly_failure.4157.base$我们可以用逆向工程技术研究它。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4157.maxed.desc:0 "$anomaly_failure.4157.base$.\n\nWhile not being that useful to us, there were also data on the civilization's culture and history, which could give us more insight into who they were."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4157.maxed.desc:0 "$anomaly_failure.4157.base$.\n\n虽然意义不大，但这个文明的文化历史数据可以让我们更了解他们的真面目。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4158.desc:0 "After opening the container we found on [WarriorHomePlanet.GetName] we were shocked to realize that it was a dispenser for a biological weapon!\n\nThe bio-weapon was made to target fertility functions and quickly spreads. It is however not entirely compatible with our DNA, and will not cause us to diminish in numbers."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4158.desc:0 "打开 [WarriorHomePlanet.GetName] 上发现的容器后，我们才意识到那是一个生物武器的发射器。\n\n这种生物武器专门降低目标的生殖能力，并且扩散迅速。不过和我们的遗传因子不兼容，所以不会影响我们种群的数量。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4158.a.tooltip:0 "§YYour Empire§! gains the §RFertility Inhibiting Bio-Weapon§! modifier."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4158.a.tooltip:0 "§Y帝国§!获得§R抑制繁衍生物武器§!的修正。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4170.base.desc:0 "The gas mining facility on [From.GetName] has turned into a burning inferno. The report says that the highly volatile gas was exposed an open flame, causing multiple facilities to explode! This in turn caused a chain reaction and blew up most of the gas caches we had located."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4170.base.desc:0 " [From.GetName] 上的气体开采设施已经化为一片火海。据报道，那种高度易燃的气体遇到了明火，导致了许多设施的爆炸！经过一连串的连锁反应，几乎炸光了我们侦探到的所有气体矿藏。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4170.individ.desc:0 "$anomaly_failure.4170.base.desc$\n\nThis backlash cannot be allowed to be repeated."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4170.individ.desc:0 "$anomaly_failure.4170.base.desc$\n\n不能再犯同样的错误了。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4170.basic.desc:0 "$anomaly_failure.4170.base.desc$\n\nThe people who died in the explosion won't be forgotten."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4170.basic.desc:0 "$anomaly_failure.4170.base.desc$\n\n我们会缅怀在爆炸中死去的同胞。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4170.base.tooltip:0 "Removes the modifier §Y"Rich Gas Mining"§! from [From.GetName]"
CN2 anomaly_failure.4170.base.tooltip:0 " [From.GetName] 失去§Y“无节制气体开采”§!的修正"
ADD anomaly_failure.4170.a.tooltip:0 "$anomaly_failure.4170.base.tooltip$."
CN2 anomaly_failure.4170.a.tooltip:0 "$anomaly_failure.4170.base.tooltip$。"
ADD anomaly_failure.4170.b.tooltip:0 "$anomaly_failure.4170.base.tooltip$ and kills §R1§! Pops."
